740 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3 && __PYX_DEFAULT_STRING_ENCODING_IS_ASCII
741 static int __Pyx_sys_getdefaultencoding_not_ascii;
742 static int __Pyx_init_sys_getdefaultencoding_params(void) {
743  PyObject* sys;
744  PyObject* default_encoding = NULL;
745  PyObject* ascii_chars_u = NULL;
746  PyObject* ascii_chars_b = NULL;
747  const char* default_encoding_c;
748  sys = PyImport_ImportModule("sys");
749  if (!sys) goto bad;
750  default_encoding = PyObject_CallMethod(sys, (char*) "getdefaultencoding", NULL);
751  Py_DECREF(sys);
752  if (!default_encoding) goto bad;
753  default_encoding_c = PyBytes_AsString(default_encoding);
754  if (!default_encoding_c) goto bad;
755  if (strcmp(default_encoding_c, "ascii") == 0) {
756  __Pyx_sys_getdefaultencoding_not_ascii = 0;
757  } else {
758  char ascii_chars[128];
759  int c;
760  for (c = 0; c < 128; c++) {
761  ascii_chars[c] = c;
762  }
763  __Pyx_sys_getdefaultencoding_not_ascii = 1;
764  ascii_chars_u = PyUnicode_DecodeASCII(ascii_chars, 128, NULL);
765  if (!ascii_chars_u) goto bad;
766  ascii_chars_b = PyUnicode_AsEncodedString(ascii_chars_u, default_encoding_c, NULL);
767  if (!ascii_chars_b || !PyBytes_Check(ascii_chars_b) || memcmp(ascii_chars, PyBytes_AS_STRING(ascii_chars_b), 128) != 0) {
768  PyErr_Format(
769  PyExc_ValueError,
770  "This module compiled with c_string_encoding=ascii, but default encoding '%.200s' is not a superset of ascii.",
771  default_encoding_c);
772  goto bad;
773  }
774  Py_DECREF(ascii_chars_u);
775  Py_DECREF(ascii_chars_b);
776  }
777  Py_DECREF(default_encoding);
778  return 0;
779 bad:
780  Py_XDECREF(default_encoding);
781  Py_XDECREF(ascii_chars_u);
782  Py_XDECREF(ascii_chars_b);
783  return -1;
784 }
785 #endif
786 #if __PYX_DEFAULT_STRING_ENCODING_IS_DEFAULT && PY_MAJOR_VERSION >= 3

788 #else

790 #if __PYX_DEFAULT_STRING_ENCODING_IS_DEFAULT

793  PyObject* sys;
794  PyObject* default_encoding = NULL;
795  char* default_encoding_c;
796  sys = PyImport_ImportModule("sys");
797  if (!sys) goto bad;
798  default_encoding = PyObject_CallMethod(sys, (char*) (const char*) "getdefaultencoding", NULL);
799  Py_DECREF(sys);
800  if (!default_encoding) goto bad;
801  default_encoding_c = PyBytes_AsString(default_encoding);
802  if (!default_encoding_c) goto bad;
803  __PYX_DEFAULT_STRING_ENCODING = (char*) malloc(strlen(default_encoding_c) + 1);
804  if (!__PYX_DEFAULT_STRING_ENCODING) goto bad;
805  strcpy(__PYX_DEFAULT_STRING_ENCODING, default_encoding_c);
806  Py_DECREF(default_encoding);
807  return 0;
808 bad:
809  Py_XDECREF(default_encoding);

811 }

915 /* Atomics.proto */
916 #include <pythread.h>
917 #ifndef CYTHON_ATOMICS
918  #define CYTHON_ATOMICS 1
919 #endif
920 #define __pyx_atomic_int_type int
921 #if CYTHON_ATOMICS && __GNUC__ >= 4 && (__GNUC_MINOR__ > 1 ||\
922  (__GNUC_MINOR__ == 1 && __GNUC_PATCHLEVEL >= 2)) &&\
923  !defined(__i386__)
924  #define __pyx_atomic_incr_aligned(value, lock) __sync_fetch_and_add(value, 1)
925  #define __pyx_atomic_decr_aligned(value, lock) __sync_fetch_and_sub(value, 1)
926  #ifdef __PYX_DEBUG_ATOMICS
927  #warning "Using GNU atomics"
928  #endif
929 #elif CYTHON_ATOMICS && defined(_MSC_VER) && 0
930  #include <Windows.h>
931  #undef __pyx_atomic_int_type
932  #define __pyx_atomic_int_type LONG
933  #define __pyx_atomic_incr_aligned(value, lock) InterlockedIncrement(value)
934  #define __pyx_atomic_decr_aligned(value, lock) InterlockedDecrement(value)
935  #ifdef __PYX_DEBUG_ATOMICS
936  #pragma message ("Using MSVC atomics")
937  #endif
938 #elif CYTHON_ATOMICS && (defined(__ICC) || defined(__INTEL_COMPILER)) && 0
939  #define __pyx_atomic_incr_aligned(value, lock) _InterlockedIncrement(value)
940  #define __pyx_atomic_decr_aligned(value, lock) _InterlockedDecrement(value)
941  #ifdef __PYX_DEBUG_ATOMICS
942  #warning "Using Intel atomics"
943  #endif
944 #else
945  #undef CYTHON_ATOMICS
946  #define CYTHON_ATOMICS 0
947  #ifdef __PYX_DEBUG_ATOMICS
948  #warning "Not using atomics"
949  #endif
950 #endif
951 typedef volatile __pyx_atomic_int_type __pyx_atomic_int;
952 #if CYTHON_ATOMICS
953  #define __pyx_add_acquisition_count(memview)\
954  __pyx_atomic_incr_aligned(__pyx_get_slice_count_pointer(memview), memview->lock)
955  #define __pyx_sub_acquisition_count(memview)\
956  __pyx_atomic_decr_aligned(__pyx_get_slice_count_pointer(memview), memview->lock)
957 #else
958  #define __pyx_add_acquisition_count(memview)\
959  __pyx_add_acquisition_count_locked(__pyx_get_slice_count_pointer(memview), memview->lock)
960  #define __pyx_sub_acquisition_count(memview)\
961  __pyx_sub_acquisition_count_locked(__pyx_get_slice_count_pointer(memview), memview->lock)
962 #endif

1383 #if CYTHON_REFNANNY

1386  void (*DECREF)(void*, PyObject*, int);
1387  void (*GOTREF)(void*, PyObject*, int);
1388  void (*GIVEREF)(void*, PyObject*, int);
1389  void* (*SetupContext)(const char*, int, const char*);
1390  void (*FinishContext)(void**);
1391  } __Pyx_RefNannyAPIStruct;
1392  static __Pyx_RefNannyAPIStruct *__Pyx_RefNanny = NULL;
1393  static __Pyx_RefNannyAPIStruct *__Pyx_RefNannyImportAPI(const char *modname);
1394  #define __Pyx_RefNannyDeclarations void *__pyx_refnanny = NULL;
1395 #ifdef WITH_THREAD
1396  #define __Pyx_RefNannySetupContext(name, acquire_gil)\
1397  if (acquire_gil) {\
1398  PyGILState_STATE __pyx_gilstate_save = PyGILState_Ensure();\
1399  __pyx_refnanny = __Pyx_RefNanny->SetupContext((name), __LINE__, __FILE__);\
1400  PyGILState_Release(__pyx_gilstate_save);\
1401  } else {\
1402  __pyx_refnanny = __Pyx_RefNanny->SetupContext((name), __LINE__, __FILE__);\
1403  }
1404 #else

1406  __pyx_refnanny = __Pyx_RefNanny->SetupContext((name), __LINE__, __FILE__)
1407 #endif
1408  #define __Pyx_RefNannyFinishContext()\
1409  __Pyx_RefNanny->FinishContext(&__pyx_refnanny)
1410  #define __Pyx_INCREF(r) __Pyx_RefNanny->INCREF(__pyx_refnanny, (PyObject *)(r), __LINE__)
1411  #define __Pyx_DECREF(r) __Pyx_RefNanny->DECREF(__pyx_refnanny, (PyObject *)(r), __LINE__)
1412  #define __Pyx_GOTREF(r) __Pyx_RefNanny->GOTREF(__pyx_refnanny, (PyObject *)(r), __LINE__)
1413  #define __Pyx_GIVEREF(r) __Pyx_RefNanny->GIVEREF(__pyx_refnanny, (PyObject *)(r), __LINE__)
1414  #define __Pyx_XINCREF(r) do { if((r) != NULL) {__Pyx_INCREF(r); }} while(0)
1415  #define __Pyx_XDECREF(r) do { if((r) != NULL) {__Pyx_DECREF(r); }} while(0)
1416  #define __Pyx_XGOTREF(r) do { if((r) != NULL) {__Pyx_GOTREF(r); }} while(0)
1417  #define __Pyx_XGIVEREF(r) do { if((r) != NULL) {__Pyx_GIVEREF(r);}} while(0)
1418 #else
1419  #define __Pyx_RefNannyDeclarations
1420  #define __Pyx_RefNannySetupContext(name, acquire_gil)
1421  #define __Pyx_RefNannyFinishContext()
1422  #define __Pyx_INCREF(r) Py_INCREF(r)
1423  #define __Pyx_DECREF(r) Py_DECREF(r)
1424  #define __Pyx_GOTREF(r)
1425  #define __Pyx_GIVEREF(r)
1426  #define __Pyx_XINCREF(r) Py_XINCREF(r)
1427  #define __Pyx_XDECREF(r) Py_XDECREF(r)
1428  #define __Pyx_XGOTREF(r)
1429  #define __Pyx_XGIVEREF(r)
1430 #endif
1431 #define __Pyx_XDECREF_SET(r, v) do {\
1432  PyObject *tmp = (PyObject *) r;\
1433  r = v; __Pyx_XDECREF(tmp);\
1434  } while (0)
1435 #define __Pyx_DECREF_SET(r, v) do {\

22742 /* RaiseArgTupleInvalid */
22743 static void __Pyx_RaiseArgtupleInvalid(
22744  const char* func_name,
22745  int exact,
22746  Py_ssize_t num_min,
22747  Py_ssize_t num_max,
22748  Py_ssize_t num_found)
22749 {
22750  Py_ssize_t num_expected;
22751  const char *more_or_less;
22752  if (num_found < num_min) {
22753  num_expected = num_min;
22754  more_or_less = "at least";
22755  } else {
22756  num_expected = num_max;
22757  more_or_less = "at most";
22758  }
22759  if (exact) {
22760  more_or_less = "exactly";
22761  }
22762  PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
22763  "%.200s() takes %.8s %" CYTHON_FORMAT_SSIZE_T "d positional argument%.1s (%" CYTHON_FORMAT_SSIZE_T "d given)",
22764  func_name, more_or_less, num_expected,
22765  (num_expected == 1) ? "" : "s", num_found);
22766 }

22769 static void __Pyx_RaiseDoubleKeywordsError(
22770  const char* func_name,
22771  PyObject* kw_name)
22772 {
22773  PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
22774  #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION >= 3
22775  "%s() got multiple values for keyword argument '%U'", func_name, kw_name);
22776  #else
22777  "%s() got multiple values for keyword argument '%s'", func_name,
22778  PyString_AsString(kw_name));
22779  #endif
22780 }

22782 /* ParseKeywords */
22783 static int __Pyx_ParseOptionalKeywords(
22784  PyObject *kwds,
22785  PyObject **argnames[],
22786  PyObject *kwds2,
22787  PyObject *values[],
22788  Py_ssize_t num_pos_args,
22789  const char* function_name)
22790 {
22791  PyObject *key = 0, *value = 0;
22792  Py_ssize_t pos = 0;
22793  PyObject*** name;
22794  PyObject*** first_kw_arg = argnames + num_pos_args;
22795  while (PyDict_Next(kwds, &pos, &key, &value)) {
22796  name = first_kw_arg;
22797  while (*name && (**name != key)) name++;
22798  if (*name) {
22799  values[name-argnames] = value;
22800  continue;
22801  }
22802  name = first_kw_arg;
22803  #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
22804  if (likely(PyString_CheckExact(key)) || likely(PyString_Check(key))) {
22805  while (*name) {
22806  if ((CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_PYPY || PyString_GET_SIZE(**name) == PyString_GET_SIZE(key))
22807  && _PyString_Eq(**name, key)) {
22808  values[name-argnames] = value;
22809  break;
22810  }
22811  name++;
22812  }
22813  if (*name) continue;
22814  else {
22815  PyObject*** argname = argnames;
22816  while (argname != first_kw_arg) {
22817  if ((**argname == key) || (
22818  (CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_PYPY || PyString_GET_SIZE(**argname) == PyString_GET_SIZE(key))
22819  && _PyString_Eq(**argname, key))) {
22820  goto arg_passed_twice;
22821  }
22822  argname++;
22823  }
22824  }
22825  } else
22826  #endif
22827  if (likely(PyUnicode_Check(key))) {
22828  while (*name) {
22829  int cmp = (**name == key) ? 0 :
22830  #if !CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_PYPY && PY_MAJOR_VERSION >= 3
22831  (PyUnicode_GET_SIZE(**name) != PyUnicode_GET_SIZE(key)) ? 1 :
22832  #endif
22833  PyUnicode_Compare(**name, key);
22834  if (cmp < 0 && unlikely(PyErr_Occurred())) goto bad;
22835  if (cmp == 0) {
22836  values[name-argnames] = value;
22837  break;
22838  }
22839  name++;
22840  }
22841  if (*name) continue;
22842  else {
22843  PyObject*** argname = argnames;
22844  while (argname != first_kw_arg) {
22845  int cmp = (**argname == key) ? 0 :
22846  #if !CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_PYPY && PY_MAJOR_VERSION >= 3
22847  (PyUnicode_GET_SIZE(**argname) != PyUnicode_GET_SIZE(key)) ? 1 :
22848  #endif
22849  PyUnicode_Compare(**argname, key);
22850  if (cmp < 0 && unlikely(PyErr_Occurred())) goto bad;
22851  if (cmp == 0) goto arg_passed_twice;
22852  argname++;
22853  }
22854  }
22855  } else
22856  goto invalid_keyword_type;
22857  if (kwds2) {
22858  if (unlikely(PyDict_SetItem(kwds2, key, value))) goto bad;
22859  } else {
22860  goto invalid_keyword;
22861  }
22862  }
22863  return 0;
22864 arg_passed_twice:
22865  __Pyx_RaiseDoubleKeywordsError(function_name, key);
22866  goto bad;
22867 invalid_keyword_type:
22868  PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
22869  "%.200s() keywords must be strings", function_name);
22870  goto bad;
22871 invalid_keyword:
22872  PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
22873  #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
22874  "%.200s() got an unexpected keyword argument '%.200s'",
22875  function_name, PyString_AsString(key));
22876  #else
22877  "%s() got an unexpected keyword argument '%U'",
22878  function_name, key);
22879  #endif
22880 bad:
22881  return -1;
22882 }

22896  if (likely(result)) {

22973 /* SliceObject */
22974 static CYTHON_INLINE int __Pyx_PyObject_SetSlice(PyObject* obj, PyObject* value,
22975  Py_ssize_t cstart, Py_ssize_t cstop,
22976  PyObject** _py_start, PyObject** _py_stop, PyObject** _py_slice,
22977  int has_cstart, int has_cstop, CYTHON_UNUSED int wraparound) {
22978 #if CYTHON_USE_TYPE_SLOTS
22979  PyMappingMethods* mp;
22980 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
22981  PySequenceMethods* ms = Py_TYPE(obj)->tp_as_sequence;
22982  if (likely(ms && ms->sq_ass_slice)) {
22983  if (!has_cstart) {
22984  if (_py_start && (*_py_start != Py_None)) {
22985  cstart = __Pyx_PyIndex_AsSsize_t(*_py_start);
22986  if ((cstart == (Py_ssize_t)-1) && PyErr_Occurred()) goto bad;
22987  } else
22988  cstart = 0;
22989  }
22990  if (!has_cstop) {
22991  if (_py_stop && (*_py_stop != Py_None)) {
22992  cstop = __Pyx_PyIndex_AsSsize_t(*_py_stop);
22993  if ((cstop == (Py_ssize_t)-1) && PyErr_Occurred()) goto bad;
22994  } else
22995  cstop = PY_SSIZE_T_MAX;
22996  }
22997  if (wraparound && unlikely((cstart < 0) | (cstop < 0)) && likely(ms->sq_length)) {
22998  Py_ssize_t l = ms->sq_length(obj);
22999  if (likely(l >= 0)) {
23000  if (cstop < 0) {
23001  cstop += l;
23002  if (cstop < 0) cstop = 0;
23003  }
23004  if (cstart < 0) {
23005  cstart += l;
23006  if (cstart < 0) cstart = 0;
23007  }
23008  } else {
23009  if (!PyErr_ExceptionMatches(PyExc_OverflowError))
23010  goto bad;
23011  PyErr_Clear();
23012  }
23013  }
23014  return ms->sq_ass_slice(obj, cstart, cstop, value);
23015  }
23016 #endif
23017  mp = Py_TYPE(obj)->tp_as_mapping;
23018  if (likely(mp && mp->mp_ass_subscript))
23019 #endif
23020  {
23021  int result;
23022  PyObject *py_slice, *py_start, *py_stop;
23023  if (_py_slice) {
23024  py_slice = *_py_slice;
23025  } else {
23026  PyObject* owned_start = NULL;
23027  PyObject* owned_stop = NULL;
23028  if (_py_start) {
23029  py_start = *_py_start;
23030  } else {
23031  if (has_cstart) {
23032  owned_start = py_start = PyInt_FromSsize_t(cstart);
23033  if (unlikely(!py_start)) goto bad;
23034  } else
23035  py_start = Py_None;
23036  }
23037  if (_py_stop) {
23038  py_stop = *_py_stop;
23039  } else {
23040  if (has_cstop) {
23041  owned_stop = py_stop = PyInt_FromSsize_t(cstop);
23042  if (unlikely(!py_stop)) {
23043  Py_XDECREF(owned_start);
23044  goto bad;
23045  }
23046  } else
23047  py_stop = Py_None;
23048  }
23049  py_slice = PySlice_New(py_start, py_stop, Py_None);
23050  Py_XDECREF(owned_start);
23051  Py_XDECREF(owned_stop);
23052  if (unlikely(!py_slice)) goto bad;
23053  }
23054 #if CYTHON_USE_TYPE_SLOTS
23055  result = mp->mp_ass_subscript(obj, py_slice, value);
23056 #else
23057  result = value ? PyObject_SetItem(obj, py_slice, value) : PyObject_DelItem(obj, py_slice);
23058 #endif
23059  if (!_py_slice) {
23060  Py_DECREF(py_slice);
23061  }
23062  return result;
23063  }
23064  PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
23065  "'%.200s' object does not support slice %.10s",
23066  Py_TYPE(obj)->tp_name, value ? "assignment" : "deletion");
23067 bad:
23068  return -1;
23069 }

23071 /* PyCFunctionFastCall */
23072 #if CYTHON_FAST_PYCCALL
23073 static CYTHON_INLINE PyObject * __Pyx_PyCFunction_FastCall(PyObject *func_obj, PyObject **args, Py_ssize_t nargs) {
23074  PyCFunctionObject *func = (PyCFunctionObject*)func_obj;
23075  PyCFunction meth = PyCFunction_GET_FUNCTION(func);
23076  PyObject *self = PyCFunction_GET_SELF(func);
23077  int flags = PyCFunction_GET_FLAGS(func);
23078  assert(PyCFunction_Check(func));
23079  assert(METH_FASTCALL == (flags & ~(METH_CLASS | METH_STATIC | METH_COEXIST | METH_KEYWORDS | METH_STACKLESS)));
23080  assert(nargs >= 0);
23081  assert(nargs == 0 || args != NULL);
23082  /* _PyCFunction_FastCallDict() must not be called with an exception set,
23083  because it may clear it (directly or indirectly) and so the
23084  caller loses its exception */
23085  assert(!PyErr_Occurred());
23086  if ((PY_VERSION_HEX < 0x030700A0) || unlikely(flags & METH_KEYWORDS)) {
23087  return (*((__Pyx_PyCFunctionFastWithKeywords)(void*)meth)) (self, args, nargs, NULL);
23088  } else {
23089  return (*((__Pyx_PyCFunctionFast)(void*)meth)) (self, args, nargs);
23090  }
23091 }

23094 /* PyFunctionFastCall */
23095 #if CYTHON_FAST_PYCALL
23096 static PyObject* __Pyx_PyFunction_FastCallNoKw(PyCodeObject *co, PyObject **args, Py_ssize_t na,
23097  PyObject *globals) {
23098  PyFrameObject *f;
23099  PyThreadState *tstate = __Pyx_PyThreadState_Current;
23100  PyObject **fastlocals;
23101  Py_ssize_t i;
23102  PyObject *result;
23103  assert(globals != NULL);
23104  /* XXX Perhaps we should create a specialized
23105  PyFrame_New() that doesn't take locals, but does
23106  take builtins without sanity checking them.
23107  */
23108  assert(tstate != NULL);
23109  f = PyFrame_New(tstate, co, globals, NULL);
23110  if (f == NULL) {
23111  return NULL;
23112  }
23113  fastlocals = __Pyx_PyFrame_GetLocalsplus(f);
23114  for (i = 0; i < na; i++) {
23115  Py_INCREF(*args);
23116  fastlocals[i] = *args++;
23117  }
23118  result = PyEval_EvalFrameEx(f,0);
23119  ++tstate->recursion_depth;
23120  Py_DECREF(f);
23121  --tstate->recursion_depth;
23122  return result;
23123 }
23124 #if 1 || PY_VERSION_HEX < 0x030600B1
23125 static PyObject *__Pyx_PyFunction_FastCallDict(PyObject *func, PyObject **args, int nargs, PyObject *kwargs) {
23126  PyCodeObject *co = (PyCodeObject *)PyFunction_GET_CODE(func);
23127  PyObject *globals = PyFunction_GET_GLOBALS(func);
23128  PyObject *argdefs = PyFunction_GET_DEFAULTS(func);
23129  PyObject *closure;
23130 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION >= 3
23131  PyObject *kwdefs;
23132 #endif
23133  PyObject *kwtuple, **k;
23134  PyObject **d;
23135  Py_ssize_t nd;
23136  Py_ssize_t nk;
23137  PyObject *result;
23138  assert(kwargs == NULL || PyDict_Check(kwargs));
23139  nk = kwargs ? PyDict_Size(kwargs) : 0;
23140  if (Py_EnterRecursiveCall((char*)" while calling a Python object")) {
23141  return NULL;
23142  }
23143  if (
23144 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION >= 3
23145  co->co_kwonlyargcount == 0 &&
23146 #endif
23147  likely(kwargs == NULL || nk == 0) &&
23148  co->co_flags == (CO_OPTIMIZED | CO_NEWLOCALS | CO_NOFREE)) {
23149  if (argdefs == NULL && co->co_argcount == nargs) {
23150  result = __Pyx_PyFunction_FastCallNoKw(co, args, nargs, globals);
23151  goto done;
23152  }
23153  else if (nargs == 0 && argdefs != NULL
23154  && co->co_argcount == Py_SIZE(argdefs)) {
23155  /* function called with no arguments, but all parameters have
23156  a default value: use default values as arguments .*/
23157  args = &PyTuple_GET_ITEM(argdefs, 0);
23158  result =__Pyx_PyFunction_FastCallNoKw(co, args, Py_SIZE(argdefs), globals);
23159  goto done;
23160  }
23161  }
23162  if (kwargs != NULL) {
23163  Py_ssize_t pos, i;
23164  kwtuple = PyTuple_New(2 * nk);
23165  if (kwtuple == NULL) {
23166  result = NULL;
23167  goto done;
23168  }
23169  k = &PyTuple_GET_ITEM(kwtuple, 0);
23170  pos = i = 0;
23171  while (PyDict_Next(kwargs, &pos, &k[i], &k[i+1])) {
23172  Py_INCREF(k[i]);
23173  Py_INCREF(k[i+1]);
23174  i += 2;
23175  }
23176  nk = i / 2;
23177  }
23178  else {
23179  kwtuple = NULL;
23180  k = NULL;
23181  }
23182  closure = PyFunction_GET_CLOSURE(func);
23183 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION >= 3
23184  kwdefs = PyFunction_GET_KW_DEFAULTS(func);
23185 #endif
23186  if (argdefs != NULL) {
23187  d = &PyTuple_GET_ITEM(argdefs, 0);
23188  nd = Py_SIZE(argdefs);
23189  }
23190  else {
23191  d = NULL;
23192  nd = 0;
23193  }
23194 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION >= 3
23195  result = PyEval_EvalCodeEx((PyObject*)co, globals, (PyObject *)NULL,
23196  args, nargs,
23197  k, (int)nk,
23198  d, (int)nd, kwdefs, closure);
23199 #else
23200  result = PyEval_EvalCodeEx(co, globals, (PyObject *)NULL,
23201  args, nargs,
23202  k, (int)nk,
23203  d, (int)nd, closure);
23204 #endif
23205  Py_XDECREF(kwtuple);
23206 done:
23207  Py_LeaveRecursiveCall();
23208  return result;
23209 }
23210 #endif
23211 #endif
23212 
23213 /* PyObjectCall2Args */
23214 static CYTHON_UNUSED PyObject* __Pyx_PyObject_Call2Args(PyObject* function, PyObject* arg1, PyObject* arg2) {
23215  PyObject *args, *result = NULL;
23216  #if CYTHON_FAST_PYCALL
23217  if (PyFunction_Check(function)) {
23218  PyObject *args[2] = {arg1, arg2};
23219  return __Pyx_PyFunction_FastCall(function, args, 2);
23220  }
23221  #endif
23222  #if CYTHON_FAST_PYCCALL
23223  if (__Pyx_PyFastCFunction_Check(function)) {
23224  PyObject *args[2] = {arg1, arg2};
23225  return __Pyx_PyCFunction_FastCall(function, args, 2);
23226  }
23227  #endif
23228  args = PyTuple_New(2);
23229  if (unlikely(!args)) goto done;
23230  Py_INCREF(arg1);
23231  PyTuple_SET_ITEM(args, 0, arg1);
23232  Py_INCREF(arg2);
23233  PyTuple_SET_ITEM(args, 1, arg2);
23234  Py_INCREF(function);
23235  result = __Pyx_PyObject_Call(function, args, NULL);
23236  Py_DECREF(args);
23237  Py_DECREF(function);
23238 done:
23239  return result;
23240 }

23242 /* PyObjectCallMethO */
23243 #if CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_CPYTHON
23244 static CYTHON_INLINE PyObject* __Pyx_PyObject_CallMethO(PyObject *func, PyObject *arg) {
23245  PyObject *self, *result;
23246  PyCFunction cfunc;
23247  cfunc = PyCFunction_GET_FUNCTION(func);
23248  self = PyCFunction_GET_SELF(func);
23249  if (unlikely(Py_EnterRecursiveCall((char*)" while calling a Python object")))
23250  return NULL;
23251  result = cfunc(self, arg);
23252  Py_LeaveRecursiveCall();
23253  if (unlikely(!result) && unlikely(!PyErr_Occurred())) {
23254  PyErr_SetString(
23255  PyExc_SystemError,
23256  "NULL result without error in PyObject_Call");
23257  }
23258  return result;
23259 }

23262 /* PyObjectCallOneArg */
23263 #if CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_CPYTHON
23264 static PyObject* __Pyx__PyObject_CallOneArg(PyObject *func, PyObject *arg) {
23265  PyObject *result;
23266  PyObject *args = PyTuple_New(1);
23267  if (unlikely(!args)) return NULL;
23268  Py_INCREF(arg);
23269  PyTuple_SET_ITEM(args, 0, arg);
23270  result = __Pyx_PyObject_Call(func, args, NULL);
23271  Py_DECREF(args);
23272  return result;
23273 }
23274 static CYTHON_INLINE PyObject* __Pyx_PyObject_CallOneArg(PyObject *func, PyObject *arg) {
23275 #if CYTHON_FAST_PYCALL
23276  if (PyFunction_Check(func)) {
23277  return __Pyx_PyFunction_FastCall(func, &arg, 1);
23278  }
23279 #endif
23280  if (likely(PyCFunction_Check(func))) {
23281  if (likely(PyCFunction_GET_FLAGS(func) & METH_O)) {
23282  return __Pyx_PyObject_CallMethO(func, arg);
23283 #if CYTHON_FAST_PYCCALL
23284  } else if (PyCFunction_GET_FLAGS(func) & METH_FASTCALL) {
23285  return __Pyx_PyCFunction_FastCall(func, &arg, 1);
23286 #endif
23287  }
23288  }
23289  return __Pyx__PyObject_CallOneArg(func, arg);
23290 }
23291 #else
23292 static CYTHON_INLINE PyObject* __Pyx_PyObject_CallOneArg(PyObject *func, PyObject *arg) {
23293  PyObject *result;
23294  PyObject *args = PyTuple_Pack(1, arg);
23295  if (unlikely(!args)) return NULL;
23296  result = __Pyx_PyObject_Call(func, args, NULL);
23297  Py_DECREF(args);
23298  return result;
23299 }

23302 /* GetItemInt */
23303 static PyObject *__Pyx_GetItemInt_Generic(PyObject *o, PyObject* j) {
23304  PyObject *r;
23305  if (!j) return NULL;
23306  r = PyObject_GetItem(o, j);
23307  Py_DECREF(j);
23308  return r;
23309 }
23310 static CYTHON_INLINE PyObject *__Pyx_GetItemInt_List_Fast(PyObject *o, Py_ssize_t i,
23311  CYTHON_NCP_UNUSED int wraparound,
23312  CYTHON_NCP_UNUSED int boundscheck) {
23313 #if CYTHON_ASSUME_SAFE_MACROS && !CYTHON_AVOID_BORROWED_REFS
23314  Py_ssize_t wrapped_i = i;
23315  if (wraparound & unlikely(i < 0)) {
23316  wrapped_i += PyList_GET_SIZE(o);
23317  }
23318  if ((!boundscheck) || likely(__Pyx_is_valid_index(wrapped_i, PyList_GET_SIZE(o)))) {
23319  PyObject *r = PyList_GET_ITEM(o, wrapped_i);
23320  Py_INCREF(r);
23321  return r;
23322  }
23323  return __Pyx_GetItemInt_Generic(o, PyInt_FromSsize_t(i));
23324 #else
23325  return PySequence_GetItem(o, i);
23326 #endif
23327 }
23328 static CYTHON_INLINE PyObject *__Pyx_GetItemInt_Tuple_Fast(PyObject *o, Py_ssize_t i,
23329  CYTHON_NCP_UNUSED int wraparound,
23330  CYTHON_NCP_UNUSED int boundscheck) {
23331 #if CYTHON_ASSUME_SAFE_MACROS && !CYTHON_AVOID_BORROWED_REFS
23332  Py_ssize_t wrapped_i = i;
23333  if (wraparound & unlikely(i < 0)) {
23334  wrapped_i += PyTuple_GET_SIZE(o);
23335  }
23336  if ((!boundscheck) || likely(__Pyx_is_valid_index(wrapped_i, PyTuple_GET_SIZE(o)))) {
23337  PyObject *r = PyTuple_GET_ITEM(o, wrapped_i);
23338  Py_INCREF(r);
23339  return r;
23340  }
23341  return __Pyx_GetItemInt_Generic(o, PyInt_FromSsize_t(i));
23342 #else
23343  return PySequence_GetItem(o, i);
23344 #endif
23345 }
23346 static CYTHON_INLINE PyObject *__Pyx_GetItemInt_Fast(PyObject *o, Py_ssize_t i, int is_list,
23347  CYTHON_NCP_UNUSED int wraparound,
23348  CYTHON_NCP_UNUSED int boundscheck) {
23349 #if CYTHON_ASSUME_SAFE_MACROS && !CYTHON_AVOID_BORROWED_REFS && CYTHON_USE_TYPE_SLOTS
23350  if (is_list || PyList_CheckExact(o)) {
23351  Py_ssize_t n = ((!wraparound) | likely(i >= 0)) ? i : i + PyList_GET_SIZE(o);
23352  if ((!boundscheck) || (likely(__Pyx_is_valid_index(n, PyList_GET_SIZE(o))))) {
23353  PyObject *r = PyList_GET_ITEM(o, n);
23354  Py_INCREF(r);
23355  return r;
23356  }
23357  }
23358  else if (PyTuple_CheckExact(o)) {
23359  Py_ssize_t n = ((!wraparound) | likely(i >= 0)) ? i : i + PyTuple_GET_SIZE(o);
23360  if ((!boundscheck) || likely(__Pyx_is_valid_index(n, PyTuple_GET_SIZE(o)))) {
23361  PyObject *r = PyTuple_GET_ITEM(o, n);
23362  Py_INCREF(r);
23363  return r;
23364  }
23365  } else {
23366  PySequenceMethods *m = Py_TYPE(o)->tp_as_sequence;
23367  if (likely(m && m->sq_item)) {
23368  if (wraparound && unlikely(i < 0) && likely(m->sq_length)) {
23369  Py_ssize_t l = m->sq_length(o);
23370  if (likely(l >= 0)) {
23371  i += l;
23372  } else {
23373  if (!PyErr_ExceptionMatches(PyExc_OverflowError))
23374  return NULL;
23375  PyErr_Clear();
23376  }
23377  }
23378  return m->sq_item(o, i);
23379  }
23380  }
23381 #else
23382  if (is_list || PySequence_Check(o)) {
23383  return PySequence_GetItem(o, i);
23384  }
23385 #endif
23386  return __Pyx_GetItemInt_Generic(o, PyInt_FromSsize_t(i));
23387 }

23389 /* PyErrFetchRestore */
23390 #if CYTHON_FAST_THREAD_STATE
23391 static CYTHON_INLINE void __Pyx_ErrRestoreInState(PyThreadState *tstate, PyObject *type, PyObject *value, PyObject *tb) {
23392  PyObject *tmp_type, *tmp_value, *tmp_tb;
23393  tmp_type = tstate->curexc_type;
23394  tmp_value = tstate->curexc_value;
23395  tmp_tb = tstate->curexc_traceback;
23396  tstate->curexc_type = type;
23397  tstate->curexc_value = value;
23398  tstate->curexc_traceback = tb;
23399  Py_XDECREF(tmp_type);
23400  Py_XDECREF(tmp_value);
23401  Py_XDECREF(tmp_tb);
23402 }
23403 static CYTHON_INLINE void __Pyx_ErrFetchInState(PyThreadState *tstate, PyObject **type, PyObject **value, PyObject **tb) {
23404  *type = tstate->curexc_type;
23405  *value = tstate->curexc_value;
23406  *tb = tstate->curexc_traceback;
23407  tstate->curexc_type = 0;
23408  tstate->curexc_value = 0;
23409  tstate->curexc_traceback = 0;
23410 }

23413 /* RaiseException */
23414 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
23415 static void __Pyx_Raise(PyObject *type, PyObject *value, PyObject *tb,
23416  CYTHON_UNUSED PyObject *cause) {
23417  __Pyx_PyThreadState_declare
23418  Py_XINCREF(type);
23419  if (!value || value == Py_None)
23420  value = NULL;
23421  else
23422  Py_INCREF(value);
23423  if (!tb || tb == Py_None)
23424  tb = NULL;
23425  else {
23426  Py_INCREF(tb);
23427  if (!PyTraceBack_Check(tb)) {
23428  PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
23429  "raise: arg 3 must be a traceback or None");
23430  goto raise_error;
23431  }
23432  }
23433  if (PyType_Check(type)) {
23434 #if CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_PYPY
23435  if (!value) {
23436  Py_INCREF(Py_None);
23437  value = Py_None;
23438  }
23439 #endif
23440  PyErr_NormalizeException(&type, &value, &tb);
23441  } else {
23442  if (value) {
23443  PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
23444  "instance exception may not have a separate value");
23445  goto raise_error;
23446  }
23447  value = type;
23448  type = (PyObject*) Py_TYPE(type);
23449  Py_INCREF(type);
23450  if (!PyType_IsSubtype((PyTypeObject *)type, (PyTypeObject *)PyExc_BaseException)) {
23451  PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
23452  "raise: exception class must be a subclass of BaseException");
23453  goto raise_error;
23454  }
23455  }
23456  __Pyx_PyThreadState_assign
23457  __Pyx_ErrRestore(type, value, tb);
23458  return;
23459 raise_error:
23460  Py_XDECREF(value);
23461  Py_XDECREF(type);
23462  Py_XDECREF(tb);
23463  return;
23464 }
23465 #else
23466 static void __Pyx_Raise(PyObject *type, PyObject *value, PyObject *tb, PyObject *cause) {
23467  PyObject* owned_instance = NULL;
23468  if (tb == Py_None) {
23469  tb = 0;
23470  } else if (tb && !PyTraceBack_Check(tb)) {
23471  PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
23472  "raise: arg 3 must be a traceback or None");
23473  goto bad;
23474  }
23475  if (value == Py_None)
23476  value = 0;
23477  if (PyExceptionInstance_Check(type)) {
23478  if (value) {
23479  PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
23480  "instance exception may not have a separate value");
23481  goto bad;
23482  }
23483  value = type;
23484  type = (PyObject*) Py_TYPE(value);
23485  } else if (PyExceptionClass_Check(type)) {
23486  PyObject *instance_class = NULL;
23487  if (value && PyExceptionInstance_Check(value)) {
23488  instance_class = (PyObject*) Py_TYPE(value);
23489  if (instance_class != type) {
23490  int is_subclass = PyObject_IsSubclass(instance_class, type);
23491  if (!is_subclass) {
23492  instance_class = NULL;
23493  } else if (unlikely(is_subclass == -1)) {
23494  goto bad;
23495  } else {
23496  type = instance_class;
23497  }
23498  }
23499  }
23500  if (!instance_class) {
23501  PyObject *args;
23502  if (!value)
23503  args = PyTuple_New(0);
23504  else if (PyTuple_Check(value)) {
23505  Py_INCREF(value);
23506  args = value;
23507  } else
23508  args = PyTuple_Pack(1, value);
23509  if (!args)
23510  goto bad;
23511  owned_instance = PyObject_Call(type, args, NULL);
23512  Py_DECREF(args);
23513  if (!owned_instance)
23514  goto bad;
23515  value = owned_instance;
23516  if (!PyExceptionInstance_Check(value)) {
23517  PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
23518  "calling %R should have returned an instance of "
23519  "BaseException, not %R",
23520  type, Py_TYPE(value));
23521  goto bad;
23522  }
23523  }
23524  } else {
23525  PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
23526  "raise: exception class must be a subclass of BaseException");
23527  goto bad;
23528  }
23529  if (cause) {
23530  PyObject *fixed_cause;
23531  if (cause == Py_None) {
23532  fixed_cause = NULL;
23533  } else if (PyExceptionClass_Check(cause)) {
23534  fixed_cause = PyObject_CallObject(cause, NULL);
23535  if (fixed_cause == NULL)
23536  goto bad;
23537  } else if (PyExceptionInstance_Check(cause)) {
23538  fixed_cause = cause;
23539  Py_INCREF(fixed_cause);
23540  } else {
23541  PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
23542  "exception causes must derive from "
23543  "BaseException");
23544  goto bad;
23545  }
23546  PyException_SetCause(value, fixed_cause);
23547  }
23548  PyErr_SetObject(type, value);
23549  if (tb) {
23550 #if CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_PYPY
23551  PyObject *tmp_type, *tmp_value, *tmp_tb;
23552  PyErr_Fetch(&tmp_type, &tmp_value, &tmp_tb);
23553  Py_INCREF(tb);
23554  PyErr_Restore(tmp_type, tmp_value, tb);
23555  Py_XDECREF(tmp_tb);
23556 #else
23557  PyThreadState *tstate = __Pyx_PyThreadState_Current;
23558  PyObject* tmp_tb = tstate->curexc_traceback;
23559  if (tb != tmp_tb) {
23560  Py_INCREF(tb);
23561  tstate->curexc_traceback = tb;
23562  Py_XDECREF(tmp_tb);
23563  }
23564 #endif
23565  }
23566 bad:
23567  Py_XDECREF(owned_instance);
23568  return;
23569 }
23570 #endif
23571 
23572 /* DictGetItem */
23573 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION >= 3 && !CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_PYPY
23574 static PyObject *__Pyx_PyDict_GetItem(PyObject *d, PyObject* key) {
23575  PyObject *value;
23576  value = PyDict_GetItemWithError(d, key);
23577  if (unlikely(!value)) {
23578  if (!PyErr_Occurred()) {
23579  if (unlikely(PyTuple_Check(key))) {
23580  PyObject* args = PyTuple_Pack(1, key);
23581  if (likely(args)) {
23582  PyErr_SetObject(PyExc_KeyError, args);
23583  Py_DECREF(args);
23584  }
23585  } else {
23586  PyErr_SetObject(PyExc_KeyError, key);
23587  }
23588  }
23589  return NULL;
23590  }
23591  Py_INCREF(value);
23592  return value;
23593 }

23670 /* PyErrExceptionMatches */
23671 #if CYTHON_FAST_THREAD_STATE
23672 static int __Pyx_PyErr_ExceptionMatchesTuple(PyObject *exc_type, PyObject *tuple) {
23673  Py_ssize_t i, n;
23674  n = PyTuple_GET_SIZE(tuple);
23675 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION >= 3
23676  for (i=0; i<n; i++) {
23677  if (exc_type == PyTuple_GET_ITEM(tuple, i)) return 1;
23678  }
23679 #endif
23680  for (i=0; i<n; i++) {
23681  if (__Pyx_PyErr_GivenExceptionMatches(exc_type, PyTuple_GET_ITEM(tuple, i))) return 1;
23682  }
23683  return 0;
23684 }
23685 static CYTHON_INLINE int __Pyx_PyErr_ExceptionMatchesInState(PyThreadState* tstate, PyObject* err) {
23686  PyObject *exc_type = tstate->curexc_type;
23687  if (exc_type == err) return 1;
23688  if (unlikely(!exc_type)) return 0;
23689  if (unlikely(PyTuple_Check(err)))
23690  return __Pyx_PyErr_ExceptionMatchesTuple(exc_type, err);
23691  return __Pyx_PyErr_GivenExceptionMatches(exc_type, err);
23692 }
23693 #endif

23695 /* GetException */
23696 #if CYTHON_FAST_THREAD_STATE
23697 static int __Pyx__GetException(PyThreadState *tstate, PyObject **type, PyObject **value, PyObject **tb)
23698 #else
23699 static int __Pyx_GetException(PyObject **type, PyObject **value, PyObject **tb)
23700 #endif
23701 {
23702  PyObject *local_type, *local_value, *local_tb;
23703 #if CYTHON_FAST_THREAD_STATE
23704  PyObject *tmp_type, *tmp_value, *tmp_tb;
23705  local_type = tstate->curexc_type;
23706  local_value = tstate->curexc_value;
23707  local_tb = tstate->curexc_traceback;
23708  tstate->curexc_type = 0;
23709  tstate->curexc_value = 0;
23710  tstate->curexc_traceback = 0;
23711 #else
23712  PyErr_Fetch(&local_type, &local_value, &local_tb);
23713 #endif
23714  PyErr_NormalizeException(&local_type, &local_value, &local_tb);
23715 #if CYTHON_FAST_THREAD_STATE
23716  if (unlikely(tstate->curexc_type))
23717 #else
23718  if (unlikely(PyErr_Occurred()))
23719 #endif
23720  goto bad;
23721  #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION >= 3
23722  if (local_tb) {
23723  if (unlikely(PyException_SetTraceback(local_value, local_tb) < 0))
23724  goto bad;
23725  }
23726  #endif
23727  Py_XINCREF(local_tb);
23728  Py_XINCREF(local_type);
23729  Py_XINCREF(local_value);
23730  *type = local_type;
23731  *value = local_value;
23732  *tb = local_tb;
23733 #if CYTHON_FAST_THREAD_STATE
23734  #if CYTHON_USE_EXC_INFO_STACK
23735  {
23736  _PyErr_StackItem *exc_info = tstate->exc_info;
23737  tmp_type = exc_info->exc_type;
23738  tmp_value = exc_info->exc_value;
23739  tmp_tb = exc_info->exc_traceback;
23740  exc_info->exc_type = local_type;
23741  exc_info->exc_value = local_value;
23742  exc_info->exc_traceback = local_tb;
23743  }
23744  #else
23745  tmp_type = tstate->exc_type;
23746  tmp_value = tstate->exc_value;
23747  tmp_tb = tstate->exc_traceback;
23748  tstate->exc_type = local_type;
23749  tstate->exc_value = local_value;
23750  tstate->exc_traceback = local_tb;
23751  #endif
23752  Py_XDECREF(tmp_type);
23753  Py_XDECREF(tmp_value);
23754  Py_XDECREF(tmp_tb);
23755 #else
23756  PyErr_SetExcInfo(local_type, local_value, local_tb);
23757 #endif
23758  return 0;
23759 bad:
23760  *type = 0;
23761  *value = 0;
23762  *tb = 0;
23763  Py_XDECREF(local_type);
23764  Py_XDECREF(local_value);
23765  Py_XDECREF(local_tb);
23766  return -1;
23767 }
23768 
23769 /* BytesEquals */
23770 static CYTHON_INLINE int __Pyx_PyBytes_Equals(PyObject* s1, PyObject* s2, int equals) {
23771 #if CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_PYPY
23772  return PyObject_RichCompareBool(s1, s2, equals);
23773 #else
23774  if (s1 == s2) {
23775  return (equals == Py_EQ);
23776  } else if (PyBytes_CheckExact(s1) & PyBytes_CheckExact(s2)) {
23777  const char *ps1, *ps2;
23778  Py_ssize_t length = PyBytes_GET_SIZE(s1);
23779  if (length != PyBytes_GET_SIZE(s2))
23780  return (equals == Py_NE);
23781  ps1 = PyBytes_AS_STRING(s1);
23782  ps2 = PyBytes_AS_STRING(s2);
23783  if (ps1[0] != ps2[0]) {
23784  return (equals == Py_NE);
23785  } else if (length == 1) {
23786  return (equals == Py_EQ);
23787  } else {
23788  int result;
23789 #if CYTHON_USE_UNICODE_INTERNALS
23790  Py_hash_t hash1, hash2;
23791  hash1 = ((PyBytesObject*)s1)->ob_shash;
23792  hash2 = ((PyBytesObject*)s2)->ob_shash;
23793  if (hash1 != hash2 && hash1 != -1 && hash2 != -1) {
23794  return (equals == Py_NE);
23795  }
23796 #endif
23797  result = memcmp(ps1, ps2, (size_t)length);
23798  return (equals == Py_EQ) ? (result == 0) : (result != 0);
23799  }
23800  } else if ((s1 == Py_None) & PyBytes_CheckExact(s2)) {
23801  return (equals == Py_NE);
23802  } else if ((s2 == Py_None) & PyBytes_CheckExact(s1)) {
23803  return (equals == Py_NE);
23804  } else {
23805  int result;
23806  PyObject* py_result = PyObject_RichCompare(s1, s2, equals);
23807  if (!py_result)
23808  return -1;
23809  result = __Pyx_PyObject_IsTrue(py_result);
23810  Py_DECREF(py_result);
23811  return result;
23812  }
23813 #endif
23814 }
23815 
23816 /* UnicodeEquals */
23817 static CYTHON_INLINE int __Pyx_PyUnicode_Equals(PyObject* s1, PyObject* s2, int equals) {
23818 #if CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_PYPY
23819  return PyObject_RichCompareBool(s1, s2, equals);
23820 #else
23821 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
23822  PyObject* owned_ref = NULL;
23823 #endif
23824  int s1_is_unicode, s2_is_unicode;
23825  if (s1 == s2) {
23826  goto return_eq;
23827  }
23828  s1_is_unicode = PyUnicode_CheckExact(s1);
23829  s2_is_unicode = PyUnicode_CheckExact(s2);
23830 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
23831  if ((s1_is_unicode & (!s2_is_unicode)) && PyString_CheckExact(s2)) {
23832  owned_ref = PyUnicode_FromObject(s2);
23833  if (unlikely(!owned_ref))
23834  return -1;
23835  s2 = owned_ref;
23836  s2_is_unicode = 1;
23837  } else if ((s2_is_unicode & (!s1_is_unicode)) && PyString_CheckExact(s1)) {
23838  owned_ref = PyUnicode_FromObject(s1);
23839  if (unlikely(!owned_ref))
23840  return -1;
23841  s1 = owned_ref;
23842  s1_is_unicode = 1;
23843  } else if (((!s2_is_unicode) & (!s1_is_unicode))) {
23844  return __Pyx_PyBytes_Equals(s1, s2, equals);
23845  }
23846 #endif
23847  if (s1_is_unicode & s2_is_unicode) {
23848  Py_ssize_t length;
23849  int kind;
23850  void *data1, *data2;
23851  if (unlikely(__Pyx_PyUnicode_READY(s1) < 0) || unlikely(__Pyx_PyUnicode_READY(s2) < 0))
23852  return -1;
23853  length = __Pyx_PyUnicode_GET_LENGTH(s1);
23854  if (length != __Pyx_PyUnicode_GET_LENGTH(s2)) {
23855  goto return_ne;
23856  }
23857 #if CYTHON_USE_UNICODE_INTERNALS
23858  {
23859  Py_hash_t hash1, hash2;
23860  #if CYTHON_PEP393_ENABLED
23861  hash1 = ((PyASCIIObject*)s1)->hash;
23862  hash2 = ((PyASCIIObject*)s2)->hash;
23863  #else
23864  hash1 = ((PyUnicodeObject*)s1)->hash;
23865  hash2 = ((PyUnicodeObject*)s2)->hash;
23866  #endif
23867  if (hash1 != hash2 && hash1 != -1 && hash2 != -1) {
23868  goto return_ne;
23869  }
23870  }
23871 #endif
23872  kind = __Pyx_PyUnicode_KIND(s1);
23873  if (kind != __Pyx_PyUnicode_KIND(s2)) {
23874  goto return_ne;
23875  }
23876  data1 = __Pyx_PyUnicode_DATA(s1);
23877  data2 = __Pyx_PyUnicode_DATA(s2);
23878  if (__Pyx_PyUnicode_READ(kind, data1, 0) != __Pyx_PyUnicode_READ(kind, data2, 0)) {
23879  goto return_ne;
23880  } else if (length == 1) {
23881  goto return_eq;
23882  } else {
23883  int result = memcmp(data1, data2, (size_t)(length * kind));
23884  #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
23885  Py_XDECREF(owned_ref);
23886  #endif
23887  return (equals == Py_EQ) ? (result == 0) : (result != 0);
23888  }
23889  } else if ((s1 == Py_None) & s2_is_unicode) {
23890  goto return_ne;
23891  } else if ((s2 == Py_None) & s1_is_unicode) {
23892  goto return_ne;
23893  } else {
23894  int result;
23895  PyObject* py_result = PyObject_RichCompare(s1, s2, equals);
23896  #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
23897  Py_XDECREF(owned_ref);
23898  #endif
23899  if (!py_result)
23900  return -1;
23901  result = __Pyx_PyObject_IsTrue(py_result);
23902  Py_DECREF(py_result);
23903  return result;
23904  }
23905 return_eq:
23906  #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
23907  Py_XDECREF(owned_ref);
23908  #endif
23909  return (equals == Py_EQ);
23910 return_ne:
23911  #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
23912  Py_XDECREF(owned_ref);
23913  #endif
23914  return (equals == Py_NE);
23915 #endif
23916 }

23918 /* None */
23919 static CYTHON_INLINE Py_ssize_t __Pyx_div_Py_ssize_t(Py_ssize_t a, Py_ssize_t b) {
23920  Py_ssize_t q = a / b;
23921  Py_ssize_t r = a - q*b;
23922  q -= ((r != 0) & ((r ^ b) < 0));
23923  return q;
23924 }

23931 #else
23932  if (likely(PyString_Check(n)))

23939 /* ObjectGetItem */
23940 #if CYTHON_USE_TYPE_SLOTS
23941 static PyObject *__Pyx_PyObject_GetIndex(PyObject *obj, PyObject* index) {
23942  PyObject *runerr;
23943  Py_ssize_t key_value;
23944  PySequenceMethods *m = Py_TYPE(obj)->tp_as_sequence;
23945  if (unlikely(!(m && m->sq_item))) {
23946  PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError, "'%.200s' object is not subscriptable", Py_TYPE(obj)->tp_name);
23947  return NULL;
23948  }
23949  key_value = __Pyx_PyIndex_AsSsize_t(index);
23950  if (likely(key_value != -1 || !(runerr = PyErr_Occurred()))) {
23951  return __Pyx_GetItemInt_Fast(obj, key_value, 0, 1, 1);
23952  }
23953  if (PyErr_GivenExceptionMatches(runerr, PyExc_OverflowError)) {
23954  PyErr_Clear();
23955  PyErr_Format(PyExc_IndexError, "cannot fit '%.200s' into an index-sized integer", Py_TYPE(index)->tp_name);
23956  }
23957  return NULL;
23958 }
23959 static PyObject *__Pyx_PyObject_GetItem(PyObject *obj, PyObject* key) {
23960  PyMappingMethods *m = Py_TYPE(obj)->tp_as_mapping;
23961  if (likely(m && m->mp_subscript)) {
23962  return m->mp_subscript(obj, key);
23963  }
23964  return __Pyx_PyObject_GetIndex(obj, key);
23965 }

23968 /* decode_c_string */
23969 static CYTHON_INLINE PyObject* __Pyx_decode_c_string(
23970  const char* cstring, Py_ssize_t start, Py_ssize_t stop,
23971  const char* encoding, const char* errors,
23972  PyObject* (*decode_func)(const char *s, Py_ssize_t size, const char *errors)) {
23973  Py_ssize_t length;
23974  if (unlikely((start < 0) | (stop < 0))) {
23975  size_t slen = strlen(cstring);
23976  if (unlikely(slen > (size_t) PY_SSIZE_T_MAX)) {
23977  PyErr_SetString(PyExc_OverflowError,
23978  "c-string too long to convert to Python");
23979  return NULL;
23980  }
23981  length = (Py_ssize_t) slen;
23982  if (start < 0) {
23983  start += length;
23984  if (start < 0)
23985  start = 0;
23986  }
23987  if (stop < 0)
23988  stop += length;
23989  }
23990  length = stop - start;
23991  if (unlikely(length <= 0))
23992  return PyUnicode_FromUnicode(NULL, 0);
23993  cstring += start;
23994  if (decode_func) {
23995  return decode_func(cstring, length, errors);
23996  } else {
23997  return PyUnicode_Decode(cstring, length, encoding, errors);
23998  }
23999 }

24002 static PyObject *__Pyx_GetAttr3Default(PyObject *d) {
24003  __Pyx_PyThreadState_declare
24004  __Pyx_PyThreadState_assign
24005  if (unlikely(!__Pyx_PyErr_ExceptionMatches(PyExc_AttributeError)))
24006  return NULL;
24007  __Pyx_PyErr_Clear();
24008  Py_INCREF(d);
24009  return d;
24010 }
24011 static CYTHON_INLINE PyObject *__Pyx_GetAttr3(PyObject *o, PyObject *n, PyObject *d) {
24012  PyObject *r = __Pyx_GetAttr(o, n);
24013  return (likely(r)) ? r : __Pyx_GetAttr3Default(d);
24014 }

24051 /* Import */
24052 static PyObject *__Pyx_Import(PyObject *name, PyObject *from_list, int level) {
24053  PyObject *empty_list = 0;
24054  PyObject *module = 0;
24055  PyObject *global_dict = 0;
24056  PyObject *empty_dict = 0;
24057  PyObject *list;
24058  #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
24059  PyObject *py_import;
24060  py_import = __Pyx_PyObject_GetAttrStr(__pyx_b, __pyx_n_s_import);
24061  if (!py_import)
24062  goto bad;
24063  #endif
24064  if (from_list)
24065  list = from_list;
24066  else {
24067  empty_list = PyList_New(0);
24068  if (!empty_list)
24069  goto bad;
24070  list = empty_list;
24071  }
24072  global_dict = PyModule_GetDict(__pyx_m);
24073  if (!global_dict)
24074  goto bad;
24075  empty_dict = PyDict_New();
24076  if (!empty_dict)
24077  goto bad;
24078  {
24079  #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION >= 3
24080  if (level == -1) {
24081  if (strchr(__Pyx_MODULE_NAME, '.')) {
24082  module = PyImport_ImportModuleLevelObject(
24083  name, global_dict, empty_dict, list, 1);
24084  if (!module) {
24085  if (!PyErr_ExceptionMatches(PyExc_ImportError))
24086  goto bad;
24087  PyErr_Clear();
24088  }
24089  }
24090  level = 0;
24091  }
24092  #endif
24093  if (!module) {
24094  #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
24095  PyObject *py_level = PyInt_FromLong(level);
24096  if (!py_level)
24097  goto bad;
24098  module = PyObject_CallFunctionObjArgs(py_import,
24099  name, global_dict, empty_dict, list, py_level, (PyObject *)NULL);
24100  Py_DECREF(py_level);
24101  #else
24102  module = PyImport_ImportModuleLevelObject(
24103  name, global_dict, empty_dict, list, level);
24104  #endif
24105  }
24106  }
24107 bad:
24108  #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
24109  Py_XDECREF(py_import);
24110  #endif
24111  Py_XDECREF(empty_list);
24112  Py_XDECREF(empty_dict);
24113  return module;
24114 }

24116 /* FastTypeChecks */
24117 #if CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_CPYTHON
24118 static int __Pyx_InBases(PyTypeObject *a, PyTypeObject *b) {
24119  while (a) {
24120  a = a->tp_base;
24121  if (a == b)
24122  return 1;
24123  }
24124  return b == &PyBaseObject_Type;
24125 }
24126 static CYTHON_INLINE int __Pyx_IsSubtype(PyTypeObject *a, PyTypeObject *b) {
24127  PyObject *mro;
24128  if (a == b) return 1;
24129  mro = a->tp_mro;
24130  if (likely(mro)) {
24131  Py_ssize_t i, n;
24132  n = PyTuple_GET_SIZE(mro);
24133  for (i = 0; i < n; i++) {
24134  if (PyTuple_GET_ITEM(mro, i) == (PyObject *)b)
24135  return 1;
24136  }
24137  return 0;
24138  }
24139  return __Pyx_InBases(a, b);
24140 }
24141 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION == 2
24142 static int __Pyx_inner_PyErr_GivenExceptionMatches2(PyObject *err, PyObject* exc_type1, PyObject* exc_type2) {
24143  PyObject *exception, *value, *tb;
24144  int res;
24145  __Pyx_PyThreadState_declare
24146  __Pyx_PyThreadState_assign
24147  __Pyx_ErrFetch(&exception, &value, &tb);
24148  res = exc_type1 ? PyObject_IsSubclass(err, exc_type1) : 0;
24149  if (unlikely(res == -1)) {
24150  PyErr_WriteUnraisable(err);
24151  res = 0;
24152  }
24153  if (!res) {
24154  res = PyObject_IsSubclass(err, exc_type2);
24155  if (unlikely(res == -1)) {
24156  PyErr_WriteUnraisable(err);
24157  res = 0;
24158  }
24159  }
24160  __Pyx_ErrRestore(exception, value, tb);
24161  return res;
24162 }
24163 #else
24164 static CYTHON_INLINE int __Pyx_inner_PyErr_GivenExceptionMatches2(PyObject *err, PyObject* exc_type1, PyObject *exc_type2) {
24165  int res = exc_type1 ? __Pyx_IsSubtype((PyTypeObject*)err, (PyTypeObject*)exc_type1) : 0;
24166  if (!res) {
24167  res = __Pyx_IsSubtype((PyTypeObject*)err, (PyTypeObject*)exc_type2);
24168  }
24169  return res;
24170 }
24171 #endif
24172 static int __Pyx_PyErr_GivenExceptionMatchesTuple(PyObject *exc_type, PyObject *tuple) {
24173  Py_ssize_t i, n;
24174  assert(PyExceptionClass_Check(exc_type));
24175  n = PyTuple_GET_SIZE(tuple);
24176 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION >= 3
24177  for (i=0; i<n; i++) {
24178  if (exc_type == PyTuple_GET_ITEM(tuple, i)) return 1;
24179  }
24180 #endif
24181  for (i=0; i<n; i++) {
24182  PyObject *t = PyTuple_GET_ITEM(tuple, i);
24183  #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
24184  if (likely(exc_type == t)) return 1;
24185  #endif
24186  if (likely(PyExceptionClass_Check(t))) {
24187  if (__Pyx_inner_PyErr_GivenExceptionMatches2(exc_type, NULL, t)) return 1;
24188  } else {
24189  }
24190  }
24191  return 0;
24192 }
24193 static CYTHON_INLINE int __Pyx_PyErr_GivenExceptionMatches(PyObject *err, PyObject* exc_type) {
24194  if (likely(err == exc_type)) return 1;
24195  if (likely(PyExceptionClass_Check(err))) {
24196  if (likely(PyExceptionClass_Check(exc_type))) {
24197  return __Pyx_inner_PyErr_GivenExceptionMatches2(err, NULL, exc_type);
24198  } else if (likely(PyTuple_Check(exc_type))) {
24199  return __Pyx_PyErr_GivenExceptionMatchesTuple(err, exc_type);
24200  } else {
24201  }
24202  }
24203  return PyErr_GivenExceptionMatches(err, exc_type);
24204 }
24205 static CYTHON_INLINE int __Pyx_PyErr_GivenExceptionMatches2(PyObject *err, PyObject *exc_type1, PyObject *exc_type2) {
24206  assert(PyExceptionClass_Check(exc_type1));
24207  assert(PyExceptionClass_Check(exc_type2));
24208  if (likely(err == exc_type1 || err == exc_type2)) return 1;
24209  if (likely(PyExceptionClass_Check(err))) {
24210  return __Pyx_inner_PyErr_GivenExceptionMatches2(err, exc_type1, exc_type2);
24211  }
24212  return (PyErr_GivenExceptionMatches(err, exc_type1) || PyErr_GivenExceptionMatches(err, exc_type2));
24213 }
24214 #endif

24216 /* PyIntBinop */
24217 #if !CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_PYPY
24218 static PyObject* __Pyx_PyInt_AddObjC(PyObject *op1, PyObject *op2, CYTHON_UNUSED long intval, CYTHON_UNUSED int inplace) {
24219  #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
24220  if (likely(PyInt_CheckExact(op1))) {
24221  const long b = intval;
24222  long x;
24223  long a = PyInt_AS_LONG(op1);
24224  x = (long)((unsigned long)a + b);
24225  if (likely((x^a) >= 0 || (x^b) >= 0))
24226  return PyInt_FromLong(x);
24227  return PyLong_Type.tp_as_number->nb_add(op1, op2);
24228  }
24229  #endif
24230  #if CYTHON_USE_PYLONG_INTERNALS
24231  if (likely(PyLong_CheckExact(op1))) {
24232  const long b = intval;
24233  long a, x;
24234 #ifdef HAVE_LONG_LONG
24235  const PY_LONG_LONG llb = intval;
24236  PY_LONG_LONG lla, llx;
24237 #endif
24238  const digit* digits = ((PyLongObject*)op1)->ob_digit;
24239  const Py_ssize_t size = Py_SIZE(op1);
24240  if (likely(__Pyx_sst_abs(size) <= 1)) {
24241  a = likely(size) ? digits[0] : 0;
24242  if (size == -1) a = -a;
24243  } else {
24244  switch (size) {
24245  case -2:
24246  if (8 * sizeof(long) - 1 > 2 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
24247  a = -(long) (((((unsigned long)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[0]));
24248  break;
24249 #ifdef HAVE_LONG_LONG
24250  } else if (8 * sizeof(PY_LONG_LONG) - 1 > 2 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
24251  lla = -(PY_LONG_LONG) (((((unsigned PY_LONG_LONG)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned PY_LONG_LONG)digits[0]));
24252  goto long_long;
24253 #endif
24254  }
24255  CYTHON_FALLTHROUGH;
24256  case 2:
24257  if (8 * sizeof(long) - 1 > 2 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
24258  a = (long) (((((unsigned long)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[0]));
24259  break;
24260 #ifdef HAVE_LONG_LONG
24261  } else if (8 * sizeof(PY_LONG_LONG) - 1 > 2 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
24262  lla = (PY_LONG_LONG) (((((unsigned PY_LONG_LONG)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned PY_LONG_LONG)digits[0]));
24263  goto long_long;
24264 #endif
24265  }
24266  CYTHON_FALLTHROUGH;
24267  case -3:
24268  if (8 * sizeof(long) - 1 > 3 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
24269  a = -(long) (((((((unsigned long)digits[2]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[0]));
24270  break;
24271 #ifdef HAVE_LONG_LONG
24272  } else if (8 * sizeof(PY_LONG_LONG) - 1 > 3 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
24273  lla = -(PY_LONG_LONG) (((((((unsigned PY_LONG_LONG)digits[2]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned PY_LONG_LONG)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned PY_LONG_LONG)digits[0]));
24274  goto long_long;
24275 #endif
24276  }
24277  CYTHON_FALLTHROUGH;
24278  case 3:
24279  if (8 * sizeof(long) - 1 > 3 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
24280  a = (long) (((((((unsigned long)digits[2]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[0]));
24281  break;
24282 #ifdef HAVE_LONG_LONG
24283  } else if (8 * sizeof(PY_LONG_LONG) - 1 > 3 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
24284  lla = (PY_LONG_LONG) (((((((unsigned PY_LONG_LONG)digits[2]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned PY_LONG_LONG)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned PY_LONG_LONG)digits[0]));
24285  goto long_long;
24286 #endif
24287  }
24288  CYTHON_FALLTHROUGH;
24289  case -4:
24290  if (8 * sizeof(long) - 1 > 4 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
24291  a = -(long) (((((((((unsigned long)digits[3]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[2]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[0]));
24292  break;
24293 #ifdef HAVE_LONG_LONG
24294  } else if (8 * sizeof(PY_LONG_LONG) - 1 > 4 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
24295  lla = -(PY_LONG_LONG) (((((((((unsigned PY_LONG_LONG)digits[3]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned PY_LONG_LONG)digits[2]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned PY_LONG_LONG)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned PY_LONG_LONG)digits[0]));
24296  goto long_long;
24297 #endif
24298  }
24299  CYTHON_FALLTHROUGH;
24300  case 4:
24301  if (8 * sizeof(long) - 1 > 4 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
24302  a = (long) (((((((((unsigned long)digits[3]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[2]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[0]));
24303  break;
24304 #ifdef HAVE_LONG_LONG
24305  } else if (8 * sizeof(PY_LONG_LONG) - 1 > 4 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
24306  lla = (PY_LONG_LONG) (((((((((unsigned PY_LONG_LONG)digits[3]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned PY_LONG_LONG)digits[2]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned PY_LONG_LONG)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned PY_LONG_LONG)digits[0]));
24307  goto long_long;
24308 #endif
24309  }
24310  CYTHON_FALLTHROUGH;
24311  default: return PyLong_Type.tp_as_number->nb_add(op1, op2);
24312  }
24313  }
24314  x = a + b;
24315  return PyLong_FromLong(x);
24316 #ifdef HAVE_LONG_LONG
24317  long_long:
24318  llx = lla + llb;
24319  return PyLong_FromLongLong(llx);
24320 #endif
24321 
24322 
24323  }
24324  #endif
24325  if (PyFloat_CheckExact(op1)) {
24326  const long b = intval;
24327  double a = PyFloat_AS_DOUBLE(op1);
24328  double result;
24329  PyFPE_START_PROTECT("add", return NULL)
24330  result = ((double)a) + (double)b;
24331  PyFPE_END_PROTECT(result)
24332  return PyFloat_FromDouble(result);
24333  }
24334  return (inplace ? PyNumber_InPlaceAdd : PyNumber_Add)(op1, op2);
24335 }
24336 #endif

24339 static CYTHON_INLINE void __Pyx_RaiseUnboundLocalError(const char *varname) {
24340  PyErr_Format(PyExc_UnboundLocalError, "local variable '%s' referenced before assignment", varname);
24341 }

24343 /* None */
24344 static CYTHON_INLINE long __Pyx_div_long(long a, long b) {
24345  long q = a / b;
24346  long r = a - q*b;
24347  q -= ((r != 0) & ((r ^ b) < 0));
24348  return q;
24349 }

24351 /* WriteUnraisableException */
24352 static void __Pyx_WriteUnraisable(const char *name, CYTHON_UNUSED int clineno,
24353  CYTHON_UNUSED int lineno, CYTHON_UNUSED const char *filename,
24354  int full_traceback, CYTHON_UNUSED int nogil) {
24355  PyObject *old_exc, *old_val, *old_tb;
24356  PyObject *ctx;
24357  __Pyx_PyThreadState_declare
24358 #ifdef WITH_THREAD
24359  PyGILState_STATE state;
24360  if (nogil)
24361  state = PyGILState_Ensure();
24362 #ifdef _MSC_VER
24363  else state = (PyGILState_STATE)-1;
24364 #endif
24365 #endif
24366  __Pyx_PyThreadState_assign
24367  __Pyx_ErrFetch(&old_exc, &old_val, &old_tb);
24368  if (full_traceback) {
24369  Py_XINCREF(old_exc);
24370  Py_XINCREF(old_val);
24371  Py_XINCREF(old_tb);
24372  __Pyx_ErrRestore(old_exc, old_val, old_tb);
24373  PyErr_PrintEx(1);
24374  }
24375  #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
24376  ctx = PyString_FromString(name);
24377  #else
24378  ctx = PyUnicode_FromString(name);
24379  #endif
24380  __Pyx_ErrRestore(old_exc, old_val, old_tb);
24381  if (!ctx) {
24382  PyErr_WriteUnraisable(Py_None);
24383  } else {
24384  PyErr_WriteUnraisable(ctx);
24385  Py_DECREF(ctx);
24386  }
24387 #ifdef WITH_THREAD
24388  if (nogil)
24389  PyGILState_Release(state);
24390 #endif
24391 }

24432 /* PyObject_GenericGetAttrNoDict */
24433 #if CYTHON_USE_TYPE_SLOTS && CYTHON_USE_PYTYPE_LOOKUP && PY_VERSION_HEX < 0x03070000
24434 static PyObject *__Pyx_RaiseGenericGetAttributeError(PyTypeObject *tp, PyObject *attr_name) {
24435  PyErr_Format(PyExc_AttributeError,
24436 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION >= 3
24437  "'%.50s' object has no attribute '%U'",
24438  tp->tp_name, attr_name);
24439 #else

24442 #endif

24445 static CYTHON_INLINE PyObject* __Pyx_PyObject_GenericGetAttrNoDict(PyObject* obj, PyObject* attr_name) {
24446  PyObject *descr;
24447  PyTypeObject *tp = Py_TYPE(obj);
24448  if (unlikely(!PyString_Check(attr_name))) {
24449  return PyObject_GenericGetAttr(obj, attr_name);
24450  }
24451  assert(!tp->tp_dictoffset);
24452  descr = _PyType_Lookup(tp, attr_name);
24453  if (unlikely(!descr)) {
24454  return __Pyx_RaiseGenericGetAttributeError(tp, attr_name);
24455  }
24456  Py_INCREF(descr);
24457  #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
24458  if (likely(PyType_HasFeature(Py_TYPE(descr), Py_TPFLAGS_HAVE_CLASS)))
24459  #endif
24460  {
24461  descrgetfunc f = Py_TYPE(descr)->tp_descr_get;
24462  if (unlikely(f)) {
24463  PyObject *res = f(descr, obj, (PyObject *)tp);
24464  Py_DECREF(descr);
24465  return res;
24466  }
24467  }
24468  return descr;
24469 }
24470 #endif

24482 /* SetupReduce */
24483 static int __Pyx_setup_reduce_is_named(PyObject* meth, PyObject* name) {
24484  int ret;
24485  PyObject *name_attr;
24486  name_attr = __Pyx_PyObject_GetAttrStr(meth, __pyx_n_s_name_2);
24487  if (likely(name_attr)) {
24488  ret = PyObject_RichCompareBool(name_attr, name, Py_EQ);
24489  } else {
24490  ret = -1;
24491  }
24492  if (unlikely(ret < 0)) {
24493  PyErr_Clear();
24494  ret = 0;
24495  }
24496  Py_XDECREF(name_attr);
24497  return ret;
24498 }
24499 static int __Pyx_setup_reduce(PyObject* type_obj) {
24500  int ret = 0;
24501  PyObject *object_reduce = NULL;
24502  PyObject *object_reduce_ex = NULL;
24503  PyObject *reduce = NULL;
24504  PyObject *reduce_ex = NULL;
24505  PyObject *reduce_cython = NULL;
24506  PyObject *setstate = NULL;
24507  PyObject *setstate_cython = NULL;
24508 #if CYTHON_USE_PYTYPE_LOOKUP
24509  if (_PyType_Lookup((PyTypeObject*)type_obj, __pyx_n_s_getstate)) goto GOOD;
24510 #else
24511  if (PyObject_HasAttr(type_obj, __pyx_n_s_getstate)) goto GOOD;
24512 #endif
24513 #if CYTHON_USE_PYTYPE_LOOKUP
24514  object_reduce_ex = _PyType_Lookup(&PyBaseObject_Type, __pyx_n_s_reduce_ex); if (!object_reduce_ex) goto BAD;
24515 #else
24516  object_reduce_ex = __Pyx_PyObject_GetAttrStr((PyObject*)&PyBaseObject_Type, __pyx_n_s_reduce_ex); if (!object_reduce_ex) goto BAD;
24517 #endif
24518  reduce_ex = __Pyx_PyObject_GetAttrStr(type_obj, __pyx_n_s_reduce_ex); if (unlikely(!reduce_ex)) goto BAD;
24519  if (reduce_ex == object_reduce_ex) {
24520 #if CYTHON_USE_PYTYPE_LOOKUP
24521  object_reduce = _PyType_Lookup(&PyBaseObject_Type, __pyx_n_s_reduce); if (!object_reduce) goto BAD;
24522 #else
24523  object_reduce = __Pyx_PyObject_GetAttrStr((PyObject*)&PyBaseObject_Type, __pyx_n_s_reduce); if (!object_reduce) goto BAD;
24524 #endif
24525  reduce = __Pyx_PyObject_GetAttrStr(type_obj, __pyx_n_s_reduce); if (unlikely(!reduce)) goto BAD;
24526  if (reduce == object_reduce || __Pyx_setup_reduce_is_named(reduce, __pyx_n_s_reduce_cython)) {
24527  reduce_cython = __Pyx_PyObject_GetAttrStr(type_obj, __pyx_n_s_reduce_cython); if (unlikely(!reduce_cython)) goto BAD;
24528  ret = PyDict_SetItem(((PyTypeObject*)type_obj)->tp_dict, __pyx_n_s_reduce, reduce_cython); if (unlikely(ret < 0)) goto BAD;
24529  ret = PyDict_DelItem(((PyTypeObject*)type_obj)->tp_dict, __pyx_n_s_reduce_cython); if (unlikely(ret < 0)) goto BAD;
24530  setstate = __Pyx_PyObject_GetAttrStr(type_obj, __pyx_n_s_setstate);
24531  if (!setstate) PyErr_Clear();
24532  if (!setstate || __Pyx_setup_reduce_is_named(setstate, __pyx_n_s_setstate_cython)) {
24533  setstate_cython = __Pyx_PyObject_GetAttrStr(type_obj, __pyx_n_s_setstate_cython); if (unlikely(!setstate_cython)) goto BAD;
24534  ret = PyDict_SetItem(((PyTypeObject*)type_obj)->tp_dict, __pyx_n_s_setstate, setstate_cython); if (unlikely(ret < 0)) goto BAD;
24535  ret = PyDict_DelItem(((PyTypeObject*)type_obj)->tp_dict, __pyx_n_s_setstate_cython); if (unlikely(ret < 0)) goto BAD;
24536  }
24537  PyType_Modified((PyTypeObject*)type_obj);
24538  }
24539  }
24540  goto GOOD;
24541 BAD:
24542  if (!PyErr_Occurred())
24543  PyErr_Format(PyExc_RuntimeError, "Unable to initialize pickling for %s", ((PyTypeObject*)type_obj)->tp_name);
24544  ret = -1;
24545 GOOD:
24546 #if !CYTHON_USE_PYTYPE_LOOKUP
24547  Py_XDECREF(object_reduce);
24548  Py_XDECREF(object_reduce_ex);
24549 #endif
24550  Py_XDECREF(reduce);
24551  Py_XDECREF(reduce_ex);
24552  Py_XDECREF(reduce_cython);
24553  Py_XDECREF(setstate);
24554  Py_XDECREF(setstate_cython);
24555  return ret;
24556 }

24558 /* SetVTable */
24559 static int __Pyx_SetVtable(PyObject *dict, void *vtable) {
24560 #if PY_VERSION_HEX >= 0x02070000
24561  PyObject *ob = PyCapsule_New(vtable, 0, 0);
24562 #else
24563  PyObject *ob = PyCObject_FromVoidPtr(vtable, 0);
24564 #endif
24565  if (!ob)
24566  goto bad;
24567  if (PyDict_SetItem(dict, __pyx_n_s_pyx_vtable, ob) < 0)
24568  goto bad;
24569  Py_DECREF(ob);
24570  return 0;
24571 bad:
24572  Py_XDECREF(ob);
24573  return -1;
24574 }

24576 /* TypeImport */
24577 #ifndef __PYX_HAVE_RT_ImportType
24578 #define __PYX_HAVE_RT_ImportType
24579 static PyTypeObject *__Pyx_ImportType(PyObject *module, const char *module_name, const char *class_name,
24580  size_t size, enum __Pyx_ImportType_CheckSize check_size)
24581 {
24582  PyObject *result = 0;
24583  char warning[200];
24584  Py_ssize_t basicsize;
24585 #ifdef Py_LIMITED_API
24586  PyObject *py_basicsize;
24587 #endif
24588  result = PyObject_GetAttrString(module, class_name);
24589  if (!result)
24590  goto bad;
24591  if (!PyType_Check(result)) {
24592  PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
24593  "%.200s.%.200s is not a type object",
24594  module_name, class_name);
24595  goto bad;
24596  }
24597 #ifndef Py_LIMITED_API
24598  basicsize = ((PyTypeObject *)result)->tp_basicsize;
24599 #else
24600  py_basicsize = PyObject_GetAttrString(result, "__basicsize__");
24601  if (!py_basicsize)
24602  goto bad;
24603  basicsize = PyLong_AsSsize_t(py_basicsize);
24604  Py_DECREF(py_basicsize);
24605  py_basicsize = 0;
24606  if (basicsize == (Py_ssize_t)-1 && PyErr_Occurred())
24607  goto bad;
24608 #endif
24609  if ((size_t)basicsize < size) {
24610  PyErr_Format(PyExc_ValueError,
24611  "%.200s.%.200s size changed, may indicate binary incompatibility. "
24612  "Expected %zd from C header, got %zd from PyObject",
24613  module_name, class_name, size, basicsize);
24614  goto bad;
24615  }
24616  if (check_size == __Pyx_ImportType_CheckSize_Error && (size_t)basicsize != size) {
24617  PyErr_Format(PyExc_ValueError,
24618  "%.200s.%.200s size changed, may indicate binary incompatibility. "
24619  "Expected %zd from C header, got %zd from PyObject",
24620  module_name, class_name, size, basicsize);
24621  goto bad;
24622  }
24623  else if (check_size == __Pyx_ImportType_CheckSize_Warn && (size_t)basicsize > size) {
24624  PyOS_snprintf(warning, sizeof(warning),
24625  "%s.%s size changed, may indicate binary incompatibility. "
24626  "Expected %zd from C header, got %zd from PyObject",
24627  module_name, class_name, size, basicsize);
24628  if (PyErr_WarnEx(NULL, warning, 0) < 0) goto bad;
24629  }
24630  return (PyTypeObject *)result;
24631 bad:
24632  Py_XDECREF(result);
24633  return NULL;
24634 }
24635 #endif

24637 /* CLineInTraceback */
24638 #ifndef CYTHON_CLINE_IN_TRACEBACK
24639 static int __Pyx_CLineForTraceback(PyThreadState *tstate, int c_line) {
24640  PyObject *use_cline;
24641  PyObject *ptype, *pvalue, *ptraceback;
24642 #if CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_CPYTHON
24643  PyObject **cython_runtime_dict;
24644 #endif
24645  if (unlikely(!__pyx_cython_runtime)) {
24646  return c_line;
24647  }
24648  __Pyx_ErrFetchInState(tstate, &ptype, &pvalue, &ptraceback);
24649 #if CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_CPYTHON
24650  cython_runtime_dict = _PyObject_GetDictPtr(__pyx_cython_runtime);
24651  if (likely(cython_runtime_dict)) {
24652  __PYX_PY_DICT_LOOKUP_IF_MODIFIED(
24653  use_cline, *cython_runtime_dict,
24654  __Pyx_PyDict_GetItemStr(*cython_runtime_dict, __pyx_n_s_cline_in_traceback))
24655  } else
24656 #endif
24657  {
24658  PyObject *use_cline_obj = __Pyx_PyObject_GetAttrStr(__pyx_cython_runtime, __pyx_n_s_cline_in_traceback);
24659  if (use_cline_obj) {
24660  use_cline = PyObject_Not(use_cline_obj) ? Py_False : Py_True;
24661  Py_DECREF(use_cline_obj);
24662  } else {
24663  PyErr_Clear();
24664  use_cline = NULL;
24665  }
24666  }
24667  if (!use_cline) {
24668  c_line = 0;
24669  PyObject_SetAttr(__pyx_cython_runtime, __pyx_n_s_cline_in_traceback, Py_False);
24670  }
24671  else if (use_cline == Py_False || (use_cline != Py_True && PyObject_Not(use_cline) != 0)) {
24672  c_line = 0;
24673  }
24674  __Pyx_ErrRestoreInState(tstate, ptype, pvalue, ptraceback);
24675  return c_line;
24676 }
24677 #endif

24679 /* CodeObjectCache */
24680 static int __pyx_bisect_code_objects(__Pyx_CodeObjectCacheEntry* entries, int count, int code_line) {
24681  int start = 0, mid = 0, end = count - 1;
24682  if (end >= 0 && code_line > entries[end].code_line) {
24683  return count;
24684  }
24685  while (start < end) {
24686  mid = start + (end - start) / 2;
24687  if (code_line < entries[mid].code_line) {
24688  end = mid;
24689  } else if (code_line > entries[mid].code_line) {
24690  start = mid + 1;
24691  } else {
24692  return mid;
24693  }
24694  }
24695  if (code_line <= entries[mid].code_line) {
24696  return mid;
24697  } else {
24698  return mid + 1;
24699  }
24700 }
24701 static PyCodeObject *__pyx_find_code_object(int code_line) {
24702  PyCodeObject* code_object;
24703  int pos;
24704  if (unlikely(!code_line) || unlikely(!__pyx_code_cache.entries)) {
24705  return NULL;
24706  }
24707  pos = __pyx_bisect_code_objects(__pyx_code_cache.entries, __pyx_code_cache.count, code_line);
24708  if (unlikely(pos >= __pyx_code_cache.count) || unlikely(__pyx_code_cache.entries[pos].code_line != code_line)) {
24709  return NULL;
24710  }
24711  code_object = __pyx_code_cache.entries[pos].code_object;
24712  Py_INCREF(code_object);
24713  return code_object;
24714 }
24715 static void __pyx_insert_code_object(int code_line, PyCodeObject* code_object) {
24716  int pos, i;
24717  __Pyx_CodeObjectCacheEntry* entries = __pyx_code_cache.entries;
24718  if (unlikely(!code_line)) {
24719  return;
24720  }
24721  if (unlikely(!entries)) {
24722  entries = (__Pyx_CodeObjectCacheEntry*)PyMem_Malloc(64*sizeof(__Pyx_CodeObjectCacheEntry));
24723  if (likely(entries)) {
24724  __pyx_code_cache.entries = entries;
24725  __pyx_code_cache.max_count = 64;
24726  __pyx_code_cache.count = 1;
24727  entries[0].code_line = code_line;
24728  entries[0].code_object = code_object;
24729  Py_INCREF(code_object);
24730  }
24731  return;
24732  }
24733  pos = __pyx_bisect_code_objects(__pyx_code_cache.entries, __pyx_code_cache.count, code_line);
24734  if ((pos < __pyx_code_cache.count) && unlikely(__pyx_code_cache.entries[pos].code_line == code_line)) {
24735  PyCodeObject* tmp = entries[pos].code_object;
24736  entries[pos].code_object = code_object;
24737  Py_DECREF(tmp);
24738  return;
24739  }
24740  if (__pyx_code_cache.count == __pyx_code_cache.max_count) {
24741  int new_max = __pyx_code_cache.max_count + 64;
24742  entries = (__Pyx_CodeObjectCacheEntry*)PyMem_Realloc(
24743  __pyx_code_cache.entries, (size_t)new_max*sizeof(__Pyx_CodeObjectCacheEntry));
24744  if (unlikely(!entries)) {
24745  return;
24746  }
24747  __pyx_code_cache.entries = entries;
24748  __pyx_code_cache.max_count = new_max;
24749  }
24750  for (i=__pyx_code_cache.count; i>pos; i--) {
24751  entries[i] = entries[i-1];
24752  }
24753  entries[pos].code_line = code_line;
24754  entries[pos].code_object = code_object;
24755  __pyx_code_cache.count++;
24756  Py_INCREF(code_object);
24757 }

24759 /* AddTraceback */
24760 #include "compile.h"
24761 #include "frameobject.h"
24762 #include "traceback.h"
24763 static PyCodeObject* __Pyx_CreateCodeObjectForTraceback(
24764  const char *funcname, int c_line,
24765  int py_line, const char *filename) {
24766  PyCodeObject *py_code = 0;
24767  PyObject *py_srcfile = 0;
24768  PyObject *py_funcname = 0;
24769  #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
24770  py_srcfile = PyString_FromString(filename);
24771  #else
24772  py_srcfile = PyUnicode_FromString(filename);
24773  #endif
24774  if (!py_srcfile) goto bad;
24775  if (c_line) {
24776  #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
24777  py_funcname = PyString_FromFormat( "%s (%s:%d)", funcname, __pyx_cfilenm, c_line);
24778  #else
24779  py_funcname = PyUnicode_FromFormat( "%s (%s:%d)", funcname, __pyx_cfilenm, c_line);
24780  #endif
24781  }
24782  else {
24783  #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
24784  py_funcname = PyString_FromString(funcname);
24785  #else
24786  py_funcname = PyUnicode_FromString(funcname);
24787  #endif
24788  }
24789  if (!py_funcname) goto bad;
24790  py_code = __Pyx_PyCode_New(
24791  0,
24792  0,
24793  0,
24794  0,
24795  0,
24796  __pyx_empty_bytes, /*PyObject *code,*/
24797  __pyx_empty_tuple, /*PyObject *consts,*/
24798  __pyx_empty_tuple, /*PyObject *names,*/
24799  __pyx_empty_tuple, /*PyObject *varnames,*/
24800  __pyx_empty_tuple, /*PyObject *freevars,*/
24801  __pyx_empty_tuple, /*PyObject *cellvars,*/
24802  py_srcfile, /*PyObject *filename,*/
24803  py_funcname, /*PyObject *name,*/
24804  py_line,
24805  __pyx_empty_bytes /*PyObject *lnotab*/
24806  );
24807  Py_DECREF(py_srcfile);
24808  Py_DECREF(py_funcname);
24809  return py_code;
24810 bad:
24811  Py_XDECREF(py_srcfile);
24812  Py_XDECREF(py_funcname);
24813  return NULL;
24814 }
24815 static void __Pyx_AddTraceback(const char *funcname, int c_line,
24816  int py_line, const char *filename) {
24817  PyCodeObject *py_code = 0;
24818  PyFrameObject *py_frame = 0;
24819  PyThreadState *tstate = __Pyx_PyThreadState_Current;
24820  if (c_line) {
24821  c_line = __Pyx_CLineForTraceback(tstate, c_line);
24822  }
24823  py_code = __pyx_find_code_object(c_line ? -c_line : py_line);
24824  if (!py_code) {
24825  py_code = __Pyx_CreateCodeObjectForTraceback(
24826  funcname, c_line, py_line, filename);
24827  if (!py_code) goto bad;
24828  __pyx_insert_code_object(c_line ? -c_line : py_line, py_code);
24829  }
24830  py_frame = PyFrame_New(
24831  tstate, /*PyThreadState *tstate,*/
24832  py_code, /*PyCodeObject *code,*/
24833  __pyx_d, /*PyObject *globals,*/
24834  0 /*PyObject *locals*/
24835  );
24836  if (!py_frame) goto bad;
24837  __Pyx_PyFrame_SetLineNumber(py_frame, py_line);
24838  PyTraceBack_Here(py_frame);
24839 bad:
24840  Py_XDECREF(py_code);
24841  Py_XDECREF(py_frame);
24842 }

24844 /* CIntFromPyVerify */
24845 #define __PYX_VERIFY_RETURN_INT(target_type, func_type, func_value)\
24846  __PYX__VERIFY_RETURN_INT(target_type, func_type, func_value, 0)
24847 #define __PYX_VERIFY_RETURN_INT_EXC(target_type, func_type, func_value)\
24848  __PYX__VERIFY_RETURN_INT(target_type, func_type, func_value, 1)
24849 #define __PYX__VERIFY_RETURN_INT(target_type, func_type, func_value, exc)\
24850  {\
24851  func_type value = func_value;\
24852  if (sizeof(target_type) < sizeof(func_type)) {\
24853  if (unlikely(value != (func_type) (target_type) value)) {\
24854  func_type zero = 0;\
24855  if (exc && unlikely(value == (func_type)-1 && PyErr_Occurred()))\
24856  return (target_type) -1;\
24857  if (is_unsigned && unlikely(value < zero))\
24858  goto raise_neg_overflow;\
24859  else\
24860  goto raise_overflow;\
24861  }\
24862  }\
24863  return (target_type) value;\
24864  }

24866 /* CIntToPy */
24867 static CYTHON_INLINE PyObject* __Pyx_PyInt_From_int(int value) {
24868  const int neg_one = (int) ((int) 0 - (int) 1), const_zero = (int) 0;
24869  const int is_unsigned = neg_one > const_zero;
24870  if (is_unsigned) {
24871  if (sizeof(int) < sizeof(long)) {
24872  return PyInt_FromLong((long) value);
24873  } else if (sizeof(int) <= sizeof(unsigned long)) {
24874  return PyLong_FromUnsignedLong((unsigned long) value);
24875 #ifdef HAVE_LONG_LONG
24876  } else if (sizeof(int) <= sizeof(unsigned PY_LONG_LONG)) {
24877  return PyLong_FromUnsignedLongLong((unsigned PY_LONG_LONG) value);
24878 #endif
24879  }
24880  } else {
24881  if (sizeof(int) <= sizeof(long)) {
24882  return PyInt_FromLong((long) value);
24883 #ifdef HAVE_LONG_LONG
24884  } else if (sizeof(int) <= sizeof(PY_LONG_LONG)) {
24885  return PyLong_FromLongLong((PY_LONG_LONG) value);
24886 #endif
24887  }
24888  }
24889  {
24890  int one = 1; int little = (int)*(unsigned char *)&one;
24891  unsigned char *bytes = (unsigned char *)&value;
24892  return _PyLong_FromByteArray(bytes, sizeof(int),
24893  little, !is_unsigned);
24894  }
24895 }

25008  static CYTHON_INLINE __pyx_t_float_complex __Pyx_c_pow_float(__pyx_t_float_complex a, __pyx_t_float_complex b) {

25012  if (b.real < 0) {

25014  a.real = a.real / denom;
25015  a.imag = -a.imag / denom;
25016  b.real = -b.real;

25219 /* CIntToPy */
25220 static CYTHON_INLINE PyObject* __Pyx_PyInt_From_enum__NPY_TYPES(enum NPY_TYPES value) {
25221  const enum NPY_TYPES neg_one = (enum NPY_TYPES) ((enum NPY_TYPES) 0 - (enum NPY_TYPES) 1), const_zero = (enum NPY_TYPES) 0;
25222  const int is_unsigned = neg_one > const_zero;
25223  if (is_unsigned) {
25224  if (sizeof(enum NPY_TYPES) < sizeof(long)) {
25225  return PyInt_FromLong((long) value);
25226  } else if (sizeof(enum NPY_TYPES) <= sizeof(unsigned long)) {
25227  return PyLong_FromUnsignedLong((unsigned long) value);
25228 #ifdef HAVE_LONG_LONG
25229  } else if (sizeof(enum NPY_TYPES) <= sizeof(unsigned PY_LONG_LONG)) {
25230  return PyLong_FromUnsignedLongLong((unsigned PY_LONG_LONG) value);
25231 #endif
25232  }
25233  } else {
25234  if (sizeof(enum NPY_TYPES) <= sizeof(long)) {
25235  return PyInt_FromLong((long) value);
25236 #ifdef HAVE_LONG_LONG
25237  } else if (sizeof(enum NPY_TYPES) <= sizeof(PY_LONG_LONG)) {
25238  return PyLong_FromLongLong((PY_LONG_LONG) value);
25239 #endif
25240  }
25241  }
25242  {
25243  int one = 1; int little = (int)*(unsigned char *)&one;
25244  unsigned char *bytes = (unsigned char *)&value;
25245  return _PyLong_FromByteArray(bytes, sizeof(enum NPY_TYPES),
25246  little, !is_unsigned);
25247  }
25248 }

25252  if (PyObject_CheckBuffer(obj)) return PyObject_GetBuffer(obj, view, flags);
25253  if (__Pyx_TypeCheck(obj, __pyx_ptype_5numpy_ndarray)) return __pyx_pw_5numpy_7ndarray_1__getbuffer__(obj, view, flags);

25274 /* MemviewSliceIsContig */
25275 static int
25276 __pyx_memviewslice_is_contig(const __Pyx_memviewslice mvs, char order, int ndim)
25277 {
25278  int i, index, step, start;
25279  Py_ssize_t itemsize = mvs.memview->view.itemsize;
25280  if (order == 'F') {
25281  step = 1;
25282  start = 0;
25283  } else {
25284  step = -1;
25285  start = ndim - 1;
25286  }
25287  for (i = 0; i < ndim; i++) {
25288  index = start + step * i;
25289  if (mvs.suboffsets[index] >= 0 || mvs.strides[index] != itemsize)
25290  return 0;
25291  itemsize *= mvs.shape[index];
25292  }
25293  return 1;
25294 }
25295 
25296 /* OverlappingSlices */
25297 static void
25298 __pyx_get_array_memory_extents(__Pyx_memviewslice *slice,
25299  void **out_start, void **out_end,
25300  int ndim, size_t itemsize)
25301 {
25302  char *start, *end;
25303  int i;
25304  start = end = slice->data;
25305  for (i = 0; i < ndim; i++) {
25306  Py_ssize_t stride = slice->strides[i];
25307  Py_ssize_t extent = slice->shape[i];
25308  if (extent == 0) {
25309  *out_start = *out_end = start;
25310  return;
25311  } else {
25312  if (stride > 0)
25313  end += stride * (extent - 1);
25314  else
25315  start += stride * (extent - 1);
25316  }
25317  }
25318  *out_start = start;
25319  *out_end = end + itemsize;
25320 }
25321 static int
25322 __pyx_slices_overlap(__Pyx_memviewslice *slice1,
25323  __Pyx_memviewslice *slice2,
25324  int ndim, size_t itemsize)
25325 {
25326  void *start1, *end1, *start2, *end2;
25327  __pyx_get_array_memory_extents(slice1, &start1, &end1, ndim, itemsize);
25328  __pyx_get_array_memory_extents(slice2, &start2, &end2, ndim, itemsize);
25329  return (start1 < end2) && (start2 < end1);
25330 }

25343 }

25345 /* CIntFromPy */
25346 static CYTHON_INLINE int __Pyx_PyInt_As_int(PyObject *x) {
25347  const int neg_one = (int) ((int) 0 - (int) 1), const_zero = (int) 0;
25348  const int is_unsigned = neg_one > const_zero;
25349 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
25350  if (likely(PyInt_Check(x))) {

25352  __PYX_VERIFY_RETURN_INT(int, long, PyInt_AS_LONG(x))
25353  } else {

25355  if (is_unsigned && unlikely(val < 0)) {
25356  goto raise_neg_overflow;
25357  }

25359  }

25375  }
25376  }
25377  break;

25380  if (8 * sizeof(unsigned long) > 3 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
25381  __PYX_VERIFY_RETURN_INT(int, unsigned long, (((((((unsigned long)digits[2]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[0])))
25382  } else if (8 * sizeof(int) >= 3 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
25383  return (int) (((((((int)digits[2]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (int)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (int)digits[0]));
25384  }
25385  }

25389  if (8 * sizeof(unsigned long) > 4 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
25390  __PYX_VERIFY_RETURN_INT(int, unsigned long, (((((((((unsigned long)digits[3]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[2]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[0])))
25391  } else if (8 * sizeof(int) >= 4 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
25392  return (int) (((((((((int)digits[3]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (int)digits[2]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (int)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (int)digits[0]));
25393  }

25401  }

25405  if (unlikely(result < 0))

25407  if (unlikely(result == 1))
25408  goto raise_neg_overflow;
25409  }
25410 #endif
25411  if (sizeof(int) <= sizeof(unsigned long)) {
25412  __PYX_VERIFY_RETURN_INT_EXC(int, unsigned long, PyLong_AsUnsignedLong(x))
25413 #ifdef HAVE_LONG_LONG
25414  } else if (sizeof(int) <= sizeof(unsigned PY_LONG_LONG)) {
25415  __PYX_VERIFY_RETURN_INT_EXC(int, unsigned PY_LONG_LONG, PyLong_AsUnsignedLongLong(x))

25474  } else if (8 * sizeof(int) - 1 > 4 * PyLong_SHIFT) {

25476  }

25478  break;

25480 #endif

25483 #ifdef HAVE_LONG_LONG
25484  } else if (sizeof(int) <= sizeof(PY_LONG_LONG)) {

25534 /* TypeInfoToFormat */
25535 static struct __pyx_typeinfo_string __Pyx_TypeInfoToFormat(__Pyx_TypeInfo *type) {
25536  struct __pyx_typeinfo_string result = { {0} };
25537  char *buf = (char *) result.string;
25538  size_t size = type->size;
25539  switch (type->typegroup) {
25540  case 'H':
25541  *buf = 'c';
25542  break;
25543  case 'I':
25544  case 'U':
25545  if (size == 1)
25546  *buf = (type->is_unsigned) ? 'B' : 'b';
25547  else if (size == 2)
25548  *buf = (type->is_unsigned) ? 'H' : 'h';
25549  else if (size == 4)
25550  *buf = (type->is_unsigned) ? 'I' : 'i';
25551  else if (size == 8)
25552  *buf = (type->is_unsigned) ? 'Q' : 'q';
25553  break;
25554  case 'P':
25555  *buf = 'P';
25556  break;
25557  case 'C':
25558  {
25559  __Pyx_TypeInfo complex_type = *type;
25560  complex_type.typegroup = 'R';
25561  complex_type.size /= 2;
25562  *buf++ = 'Z';
25563  *buf = __Pyx_TypeInfoToFormat(&complex_type).string[0];
25564  break;
25565  }
25566  case 'R':
25567  if (size == 4)
25568  *buf = 'f';
25569  else if (size == 8)
25570  *buf = 'd';
25571  else
25572  *buf = 'g';
25573  break;
25574  }
25575  return result;
25576 }

25578 /* MemviewSliceCopyTemplate */
25579 static __Pyx_memviewslice
25580 __pyx_memoryview_copy_new_contig(const __Pyx_memviewslice *from_mvs,
25581  const char *mode, int ndim,
25582  size_t sizeof_dtype, int contig_flag,
25583  int dtype_is_object)
25584 {
25585  __Pyx_RefNannyDeclarations

25589  Py_buffer *buf = &from_memview->view;

25594  __Pyx_RefNannySetupContext("__pyx_memoryview_copy_new_contig", 0);

25598  "indirect dimensions (axis %d)", i);

25600  }

25622  (PyObject *) array_obj, contig_flag,

25630  dtype_is_object) < 0))

25637 no_fail:
