25645 /* MemviewSliceInit */
25646 static int
25647 __Pyx_init_memviewslice(struct __pyx_memoryview_obj *memview,
25648  int ndim,
25649  __Pyx_memviewslice *memviewslice,
25650  int memview_is_new_reference)
25651 {
25652  __Pyx_RefNannyDeclarations
25653  int i, retval=-1;
25654  Py_buffer *buf = &memview->view;
25655  __Pyx_RefNannySetupContext("init_memviewslice", 0);
25656  if (!buf) {
25657  PyErr_SetString(PyExc_ValueError,
25658  "buf is NULL.");
25659  goto fail;
25660  } else if (memviewslice->memview || memviewslice->data) {
25661  PyErr_SetString(PyExc_ValueError,
25662  "memviewslice is already initialized!");
25663  goto fail;
25664  }
25665  if (buf->strides) {
25666  for (i = 0; i < ndim; i++) {
25667  memviewslice->strides[i] = buf->strides[i];
25668  }
25669  } else {
25670  Py_ssize_t stride = buf->itemsize;
25671  for (i = ndim - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
25672  memviewslice->strides[i] = stride;
25673  stride *= buf->shape[i];
25674  }
25675  }
25676  for (i = 0; i < ndim; i++) {
25677  memviewslice->shape[i] = buf->shape[i];
25678  if (buf->suboffsets) {
25679  memviewslice->suboffsets[i] = buf->suboffsets[i];
25680  } else {
25681  memviewslice->suboffsets[i] = -1;
25682  }
25683  }
25684  memviewslice->memview = memview;
25685  memviewslice->data = (char *)buf->buf;
25686  if (__pyx_add_acquisition_count(memview) == 0 && !memview_is_new_reference) {
25687  Py_INCREF(memview);
25688  }
25689  retval = 0;
25690  goto no_fail;
25691 fail:
25692  memviewslice->memview = 0;
25693  memviewslice->data = 0;
25694  retval = -1;
25695 no_fail:
25696  __Pyx_RefNannyFinishContext();
25697  return retval;
25698 }
25699 #ifndef Py_NO_RETURN
25700 #define Py_NO_RETURN
25701 #endif
25702 static void __pyx_fatalerror(const char *fmt, ...) Py_NO_RETURN {
25703  va_list vargs;
25704  char msg[200];
25705 #ifdef HAVE_STDARG_PROTOTYPES
25706  va_start(vargs, fmt);
25707 #else
25708  va_start(vargs);
25709 #endif
25710  vsnprintf(msg, 200, fmt, vargs);
25711  va_end(vargs);
25712  Py_FatalError(msg);
25713 }
25714 static CYTHON_INLINE int
25715 __pyx_add_acquisition_count_locked(__pyx_atomic_int *acquisition_count,
25716  PyThread_type_lock lock)
25717 {
25718  int result;
25719  PyThread_acquire_lock(lock, 1);
25720  result = (*acquisition_count)++;
25721  PyThread_release_lock(lock);
25722  return result;
25723 }
25724 static CYTHON_INLINE int
25725 __pyx_sub_acquisition_count_locked(__pyx_atomic_int *acquisition_count,
25726  PyThread_type_lock lock)
25727 {
25728  int result;
25729  PyThread_acquire_lock(lock, 1);
25730  result = (*acquisition_count)--;
25731  PyThread_release_lock(lock);
25732  return result;
25733 }
25734 static CYTHON_INLINE void
25735 __Pyx_INC_MEMVIEW(__Pyx_memviewslice *memslice, int have_gil, int lineno)
25736 {
25737  int first_time;
25738  struct __pyx_memoryview_obj *memview = memslice->memview;
25739  if (!memview || (PyObject *) memview == Py_None)
25740  return;
25741  if (__pyx_get_slice_count(memview) < 0)
25742  __pyx_fatalerror("Acquisition count is %d (line %d)",
25743  __pyx_get_slice_count(memview), lineno);
25744  first_time = __pyx_add_acquisition_count(memview) == 0;
25745  if (first_time) {
25746  if (have_gil) {
25747  Py_INCREF((PyObject *) memview);
25748  } else {
25749  PyGILState_STATE _gilstate = PyGILState_Ensure();
25750  Py_INCREF((PyObject *) memview);
25751  PyGILState_Release(_gilstate);
25752  }
25753  }
25754 }
25755 static CYTHON_INLINE void __Pyx_XDEC_MEMVIEW(__Pyx_memviewslice *memslice,
25756  int have_gil, int lineno) {
25757  int last_time;
25758  struct __pyx_memoryview_obj *memview = memslice->memview;
25759  if (!memview ) {
25760  return;
25761  } else if ((PyObject *) memview == Py_None) {
25762  memslice->memview = NULL;
25763  return;
25764  }
25765  if (__pyx_get_slice_count(memview) <= 0)
25766  __pyx_fatalerror("Acquisition count is %d (line %d)",
25767  __pyx_get_slice_count(memview), lineno);
25768  last_time = __pyx_sub_acquisition_count(memview) == 1;
25769  memslice->data = NULL;
25770  if (last_time) {
25771  if (have_gil) {
25772  Py_CLEAR(memslice->memview);
25773  } else {
25774  PyGILState_STATE _gilstate = PyGILState_Ensure();
25775  Py_CLEAR(memslice->memview);
25776  PyGILState_Release(_gilstate);
25777  }
25778  } else {
25779  memslice->memview = NULL;
25780  }
25781 }

25783 /* CIntFromPy */
25784 static CYTHON_INLINE long __Pyx_PyInt_As_long(PyObject *x) {
25785  const long neg_one = (long) ((long) 0 - (long) 1), const_zero = (long) 0;
25786  const int is_unsigned = neg_one > const_zero;
25787 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
25788  if (likely(PyInt_Check(x))) {
25789  if (sizeof(long) < sizeof(long)) {
25790  __PYX_VERIFY_RETURN_INT(long, long, PyInt_AS_LONG(x))
25791  } else {
25792  long val = PyInt_AS_LONG(x);
25793  if (is_unsigned && unlikely(val < 0)) {
25794  goto raise_neg_overflow;
25795  }
25796  return (long) val;
25797  }
25798  } else
25799 #endif
25800  if (likely(PyLong_Check(x))) {
25801  if (is_unsigned) {
25802 #if CYTHON_USE_PYLONG_INTERNALS
25803  const digit* digits = ((PyLongObject*)x)->ob_digit;
25804  switch (Py_SIZE(x)) {
25805  case 0: return (long) 0;
25806  case 1: __PYX_VERIFY_RETURN_INT(long, digit, digits[0])
25807  case 2:
25808  if (8 * sizeof(long) > 1 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
25809  if (8 * sizeof(unsigned long) > 2 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
25810  __PYX_VERIFY_RETURN_INT(long, unsigned long, (((((unsigned long)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[0])))
25811  } else if (8 * sizeof(long) >= 2 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
25812  return (long) (((((long)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (long)digits[0]));
25813  }
25814  }
25815  break;
25816  case 3:
25817  if (8 * sizeof(long) > 2 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
25818  if (8 * sizeof(unsigned long) > 3 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
25819  __PYX_VERIFY_RETURN_INT(long, unsigned long, (((((((unsigned long)digits[2]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[0])))
25820  } else if (8 * sizeof(long) >= 3 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
25821  return (long) (((((((long)digits[2]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (long)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (long)digits[0]));
25822  }
25823  }
25824  break;
25825  case 4:
25826  if (8 * sizeof(long) > 3 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
25827  if (8 * sizeof(unsigned long) > 4 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
25828  __PYX_VERIFY_RETURN_INT(long, unsigned long, (((((((((unsigned long)digits[3]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[2]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[0])))
25829  } else if (8 * sizeof(long) >= 4 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
25830  return (long) (((((((((long)digits[3]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (long)digits[2]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (long)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (long)digits[0]));
25831  }
25832  }
25833  break;
25834  }
25835 #endif
25836 #if CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_CPYTHON
25837  if (unlikely(Py_SIZE(x) < 0)) {
25838  goto raise_neg_overflow;
25839  }
25840 #else
25841  {
25842  int result = PyObject_RichCompareBool(x, Py_False, Py_LT);
25843  if (unlikely(result < 0))
25844  return (long) -1;
25845  if (unlikely(result == 1))
25846  goto raise_neg_overflow;
25847  }
25848 #endif
25849  if (sizeof(long) <= sizeof(unsigned long)) {
25850  __PYX_VERIFY_RETURN_INT_EXC(long, unsigned long, PyLong_AsUnsignedLong(x))
25851 #ifdef HAVE_LONG_LONG
25852  } else if (sizeof(long) <= sizeof(unsigned PY_LONG_LONG)) {
25853  __PYX_VERIFY_RETURN_INT_EXC(long, unsigned PY_LONG_LONG, PyLong_AsUnsignedLongLong(x))
25854 #endif
25855  }
25856  } else {
25857 #if CYTHON_USE_PYLONG_INTERNALS
25858  const digit* digits = ((PyLongObject*)x)->ob_digit;
25859  switch (Py_SIZE(x)) {
25860  case 0: return (long) 0;
25861  case -1: __PYX_VERIFY_RETURN_INT(long, sdigit, (sdigit) (-(sdigit)digits[0]))
25862  case 1: __PYX_VERIFY_RETURN_INT(long, digit, +digits[0])
25863  case -2:
25864  if (8 * sizeof(long) - 1 > 1 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
25865  if (8 * sizeof(unsigned long) > 2 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
25866  __PYX_VERIFY_RETURN_INT(long, long, -(long) (((((unsigned long)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[0])))
25867  } else if (8 * sizeof(long) - 1 > 2 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
25868  return (long) (((long)-1)*(((((long)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (long)digits[0])));
25869  }
25870  }
25871  break;
25872  case 2:
25873  if (8 * sizeof(long) > 1 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
25874  if (8 * sizeof(unsigned long) > 2 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
25875  __PYX_VERIFY_RETURN_INT(long, unsigned long, (((((unsigned long)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[0])))
25876  } else if (8 * sizeof(long) - 1 > 2 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
25877  return (long) ((((((long)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (long)digits[0])));
25878  }
25879  }
25880  break;
25881  case -3:
25882  if (8 * sizeof(long) - 1 > 2 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
25883  if (8 * sizeof(unsigned long) > 3 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
25884  __PYX_VERIFY_RETURN_INT(long, long, -(long) (((((((unsigned long)digits[2]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[0])))
25885  } else if (8 * sizeof(long) - 1 > 3 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
25886  return (long) (((long)-1)*(((((((long)digits[2]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (long)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (long)digits[0])));
25887  }
25888  }
25889  break;
25890  case 3:
25891  if (8 * sizeof(long) > 2 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
25892  if (8 * sizeof(unsigned long) > 3 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
25893  __PYX_VERIFY_RETURN_INT(long, unsigned long, (((((((unsigned long)digits[2]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[0])))
25894  } else if (8 * sizeof(long) - 1 > 3 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
25895  return (long) ((((((((long)digits[2]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (long)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (long)digits[0])));
25896  }
25897  }
25898  break;
25899  case -4:
25900  if (8 * sizeof(long) - 1 > 3 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
25901  if (8 * sizeof(unsigned long) > 4 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
25902  __PYX_VERIFY_RETURN_INT(long, long, -(long) (((((((((unsigned long)digits[3]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[2]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[0])))
25903  } else if (8 * sizeof(long) - 1 > 4 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
25904  return (long) (((long)-1)*(((((((((long)digits[3]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (long)digits[2]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (long)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (long)digits[0])));
25905  }
25906  }
25907  break;
25908  case 4:
25909  if (8 * sizeof(long) > 3 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
25910  if (8 * sizeof(unsigned long) > 4 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
25911  __PYX_VERIFY_RETURN_INT(long, unsigned long, (((((((((unsigned long)digits[3]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[2]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (unsigned long)digits[0])))
25912  } else if (8 * sizeof(long) - 1 > 4 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
25913  return (long) ((((((((((long)digits[3]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (long)digits[2]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (long)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (long)digits[0])));
25914  }
25915  }
25916  break;
25917  }
25918 #endif
25919  if (sizeof(long) <= sizeof(long)) {
25920  __PYX_VERIFY_RETURN_INT_EXC(long, long, PyLong_AsLong(x))
25921 #ifdef HAVE_LONG_LONG
25922  } else if (sizeof(long) <= sizeof(PY_LONG_LONG)) {
25923  __PYX_VERIFY_RETURN_INT_EXC(long, PY_LONG_LONG, PyLong_AsLongLong(x))
25924 #endif
25925  }
25926  }
25927  {
25928 #if CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_PYPY && !defined(_PyLong_AsByteArray)
25929  PyErr_SetString(PyExc_RuntimeError,
25930  "_PyLong_AsByteArray() not available in PyPy, cannot convert large numbers");
25931 #else

25934  #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
25935  if (likely(v) && !PyLong_Check(v)) {
25936  PyObject *tmp = v;
25937  v = PyNumber_Long(tmp);
25938  Py_DECREF(tmp);
25939  }
25940  #endif
25941  if (likely(v)) {
25942  int one = 1; int is_little = (int)*(unsigned char *)&one;
25943  unsigned char *bytes = (unsigned char *)&val;
25944  int ret = _PyLong_AsByteArray((PyLongObject *)v,
25945  bytes, sizeof(val),
25946  is_little, !is_unsigned);
25947  Py_DECREF(v);
25948  if (likely(!ret))
25949  return val;
25950  }
25951 #endif
25952  return (long) -1;
25953  }
25954  } else {
25955  long val;
25956  PyObject *tmp = __Pyx_PyNumber_IntOrLong(x);
25957  if (!tmp) return (long) -1;
25958  val = __Pyx_PyInt_As_long(tmp);
25959  Py_DECREF(tmp);
25960  return val;
25961  }
25962 raise_overflow:
25963  PyErr_SetString(PyExc_OverflowError,
25964  "value too large to convert to long");
25965  return (long) -1;
25966 raise_neg_overflow:
25967  PyErr_SetString(PyExc_OverflowError,
25968  "can't convert negative value to long");
25969  return (long) -1;
25970 }

25972 /* CIntToPy */
25973 static CYTHON_INLINE PyObject* __Pyx_PyInt_From_long(long value) {
25974  const long neg_one = (long) ((long) 0 - (long) 1), const_zero = (long) 0;
25975  const int is_unsigned = neg_one > const_zero;
25976  if (is_unsigned) {
25977  if (sizeof(long) < sizeof(long)) {
25978  return PyInt_FromLong((long) value);
25979  } else if (sizeof(long) <= sizeof(unsigned long)) {
25980  return PyLong_FromUnsignedLong((unsigned long) value);
25981 #ifdef HAVE_LONG_LONG
25982  } else if (sizeof(long) <= sizeof(unsigned PY_LONG_LONG)) {
25983  return PyLong_FromUnsignedLongLong((unsigned PY_LONG_LONG) value);
25984 #endif
25985  }
25986  } else {
25987  if (sizeof(long) <= sizeof(long)) {
25988  return PyInt_FromLong((long) value);
25989 #ifdef HAVE_LONG_LONG
25990  } else if (sizeof(long) <= sizeof(PY_LONG_LONG)) {
25991  return PyLong_FromLongLong((PY_LONG_LONG) value);
25992 #endif
25993  }
25994  }
25995  {
25996  int one = 1; int little = (int)*(unsigned char *)&one;
25997  unsigned char *bytes = (unsigned char *)&value;
25998  return _PyLong_FromByteArray(bytes, sizeof(long),
25999  little, !is_unsigned);
26000  }
26001 }

26192 /* CheckBinaryVersion */
26193 static int __Pyx_check_binary_version(void) {
26194  char ctversion[4], rtversion[4];
26195  PyOS_snprintf(ctversion, 4, "%d.%d", PY_MAJOR_VERSION, PY_MINOR_VERSION);
26196  PyOS_snprintf(rtversion, 4, "%s", Py_GetVersion());
26197  if (ctversion[0] != rtversion[0] || ctversion[2] != rtversion[2]) {
26198  char message[200];
26199  PyOS_snprintf(message, sizeof(message),
26200  "compiletime version %s of module '%.100s' "
26201  "does not match runtime version %s",
26202  ctversion, __Pyx_MODULE_NAME, rtversion);
26203  return PyErr_WarnEx(NULL, message, 1);
26204  }
26205  return 0;
26206 }

26208 /* InitStrings */
26209 static int __Pyx_InitStrings(__Pyx_StringTabEntry *t) {
26210  while (t->p) {
26211  #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
26212  if (t->is_unicode) {
26213  *t->p = PyUnicode_DecodeUTF8(t->s, t->n - 1, NULL);
26214  } else if (t->intern) {
26215  *t->p = PyString_InternFromString(t->s);
26216  } else {
26217  *t->p = PyString_FromStringAndSize(t->s, t->n - 1);
26218  }
26219  #else
26220  if (t->is_unicode | t->is_str) {
26221  if (t->intern) {
26222  *t->p = PyUnicode_InternFromString(t->s);
26223  } else if (t->encoding) {
26224  *t->p = PyUnicode_Decode(t->s, t->n - 1, t->encoding, NULL);
26225  } else {
26226  *t->p = PyUnicode_FromStringAndSize(t->s, t->n - 1);
26227  }
26228  } else {
26229  *t->p = PyBytes_FromStringAndSize(t->s, t->n - 1);
26230  }
26231  #endif
26232  if (!*t->p)
26233  return -1;
26234  if (PyObject_Hash(*t->p) == -1)
26235  return -1;
26236  ++t;
26237  }
26238  return 0;
26239 }

26244 static CYTHON_INLINE const char* __Pyx_PyObject_AsString(PyObject* o) {
26245  Py_ssize_t ignore;
26246  return __Pyx_PyObject_AsStringAndSize(o, &ignore);
26247 }
26248 #if __PYX_DEFAULT_STRING_ENCODING_IS_ASCII || __PYX_DEFAULT_STRING_ENCODING_IS_DEFAULT
26249 #if !CYTHON_PEP393_ENABLED
26250 static const char* __Pyx_PyUnicode_AsStringAndSize(PyObject* o, Py_ssize_t *length) {
26251  char* defenc_c;
26252  PyObject* defenc = _PyUnicode_AsDefaultEncodedString(o, NULL);
26253  if (!defenc) return NULL;
26254  defenc_c = PyBytes_AS_STRING(defenc);
26255 #if __PYX_DEFAULT_STRING_ENCODING_IS_ASCII
26256  {
26257  char* end = defenc_c + PyBytes_GET_SIZE(defenc);
26258  char* c;
26259  for (c = defenc_c; c < end; c++) {
26260  if ((unsigned char) (*c) >= 128) {
26261  PyUnicode_AsASCIIString(o);
26262  return NULL;
26263  }
26264  }
26265  }
26266 #endif
26267  *length = PyBytes_GET_SIZE(defenc);
26268  return defenc_c;
26269 }
26270 #else
26271 static CYTHON_INLINE const char* __Pyx_PyUnicode_AsStringAndSize(PyObject* o, Py_ssize_t *length) {
26272  if (unlikely(__Pyx_PyUnicode_READY(o) == -1)) return NULL;
26273 #if __PYX_DEFAULT_STRING_ENCODING_IS_ASCII
26274  if (likely(PyUnicode_IS_ASCII(o))) {
26275  *length = PyUnicode_GET_LENGTH(o);
26276  return PyUnicode_AsUTF8(o);
26277  } else {
26278  PyUnicode_AsASCIIString(o);
26279  return NULL;
26280  }
26281 #else
26282  return PyUnicode_AsUTF8AndSize(o, length);
26283 #endif
26284 }
26285 #endif
26286 #endif
26287 static CYTHON_INLINE const char* __Pyx_PyObject_AsStringAndSize(PyObject* o, Py_ssize_t *length) {
26288 #if __PYX_DEFAULT_STRING_ENCODING_IS_ASCII || __PYX_DEFAULT_STRING_ENCODING_IS_DEFAULT
26289  if (
26290 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3 && __PYX_DEFAULT_STRING_ENCODING_IS_ASCII
26291  __Pyx_sys_getdefaultencoding_not_ascii &&
26292 #endif
26293  PyUnicode_Check(o)) {
26294  return __Pyx_PyUnicode_AsStringAndSize(o, length);
26295  } else
26296 #endif
26297 #if (!CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_PYPY) || (defined(PyByteArray_AS_STRING) && defined(PyByteArray_GET_SIZE))
26298  if (PyByteArray_Check(o)) {
26299  *length = PyByteArray_GET_SIZE(o);
26300  return PyByteArray_AS_STRING(o);
26301  } else
26302 #endif
26303  {
26304  char* result;
26305  int r = PyBytes_AsStringAndSize(o, &result, length);
26306  if (unlikely(r < 0)) {
26307  return NULL;
26308  } else {
26309  return result;
26310  }
26311  }
26312 }
26313 static CYTHON_INLINE int __Pyx_PyObject_IsTrue(PyObject* x) {
26314  int is_true = x == Py_True;
26315  if (is_true | (x == Py_False) | (x == Py_None)) return is_true;
26316  else return PyObject_IsTrue(x);
26317 }
26318 static CYTHON_INLINE int __Pyx_PyObject_IsTrueAndDecref(PyObject* x) {
26319  int retval;
26320  if (unlikely(!x)) return -1;
26321  retval = __Pyx_PyObject_IsTrue(x);
26322  Py_DECREF(x);
26323  return retval;
26324 }
26325 static PyObject* __Pyx_PyNumber_IntOrLongWrongResultType(PyObject* result, const char* type_name) {
26326 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION >= 3
26327  if (PyLong_Check(result)) {
26328  if (PyErr_WarnFormat(PyExc_DeprecationWarning, 1,
26329  "__int__ returned non-int (type %.200s). "
26330  "The ability to return an instance of a strict subclass of int "
26331  "is deprecated, and may be removed in a future version of Python.",
26332  Py_TYPE(result)->tp_name)) {
26333  Py_DECREF(result);
26334  return NULL;
26335  }
26336  return result;
26337  }
26338 #endif
26339  PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
26340  "__%.4s__ returned non-%.4s (type %.200s)",
26341  type_name, type_name, Py_TYPE(result)->tp_name);
26342  Py_DECREF(result);
26343  return NULL;
26344 }
26345 static CYTHON_INLINE PyObject* __Pyx_PyNumber_IntOrLong(PyObject* x) {
26346 #if CYTHON_USE_TYPE_SLOTS
26347  PyNumberMethods *m;
26348 #endif
26349  const char *name = NULL;
26350  PyObject *res = NULL;
26351 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
26352  if (likely(PyInt_Check(x) || PyLong_Check(x)))
26353 #else
26354  if (likely(PyLong_Check(x)))
26355 #endif
26356  return __Pyx_NewRef(x);
26357 #if CYTHON_USE_TYPE_SLOTS
26358  m = Py_TYPE(x)->tp_as_number;
26359  #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
26360  if (m && m->nb_int) {
26361  name = "int";
26362  res = m->nb_int(x);
26363  }
26364  else if (m && m->nb_long) {
26365  name = "long";
26366  res = m->nb_long(x);
26367  }
26368  #else
26369  if (likely(m && m->nb_int)) {
26370  name = "int";
26371  res = m->nb_int(x);
26372  }
26373  #endif
26374 #else
26375  if (!PyBytes_CheckExact(x) && !PyUnicode_CheckExact(x)) {
26376  res = PyNumber_Int(x);
26377  }
26378 #endif
26379  if (likely(res)) {
26380 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
26381  if (unlikely(!PyInt_Check(res) && !PyLong_Check(res))) {
26382 #else
26383  if (unlikely(!PyLong_CheckExact(res))) {
26384 #endif
26385  return __Pyx_PyNumber_IntOrLongWrongResultType(res, name);
26386  }
26387  }
26388  else if (!PyErr_Occurred()) {
26389  PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
26390  "an integer is required");
26391  }
26392  return res;
26393 }
26394 static CYTHON_INLINE Py_ssize_t __Pyx_PyIndex_AsSsize_t(PyObject* b) {
26395  Py_ssize_t ival;
26396  PyObject *x;
26397 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
26398  if (likely(PyInt_CheckExact(b))) {
26399  if (sizeof(Py_ssize_t) >= sizeof(long))
26400  return PyInt_AS_LONG(b);
26401  else
26402  return PyInt_AsSsize_t(b);
26403  }
26404 #endif
26405  if (likely(PyLong_CheckExact(b))) {
26406  #if CYTHON_USE_PYLONG_INTERNALS
26407  const digit* digits = ((PyLongObject*)b)->ob_digit;
26408  const Py_ssize_t size = Py_SIZE(b);
26409  if (likely(__Pyx_sst_abs(size) <= 1)) {
26410  ival = likely(size) ? digits[0] : 0;
26411  if (size == -1) ival = -ival;
26412  return ival;
26413  } else {
26414  switch (size) {
26415  case 2:
26416  if (8 * sizeof(Py_ssize_t) > 2 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
26417  return (Py_ssize_t) (((((size_t)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (size_t)digits[0]));
26418  }
26419  break;
26420  case -2:
26421  if (8 * sizeof(Py_ssize_t) > 2 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
26422  return -(Py_ssize_t) (((((size_t)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (size_t)digits[0]));
26423  }
26424  break;
26425  case 3:
26426  if (8 * sizeof(Py_ssize_t) > 3 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
26427  return (Py_ssize_t) (((((((size_t)digits[2]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (size_t)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (size_t)digits[0]));
26428  }
26429  break;
26430  case -3:
26431  if (8 * sizeof(Py_ssize_t) > 3 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
26432  return -(Py_ssize_t) (((((((size_t)digits[2]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (size_t)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (size_t)digits[0]));
26433  }
26434  break;
26435  case 4:
26436  if (8 * sizeof(Py_ssize_t) > 4 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
26437  return (Py_ssize_t) (((((((((size_t)digits[3]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (size_t)digits[2]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (size_t)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (size_t)digits[0]));
26438  }
26439  break;
26440  case -4:
26441  if (8 * sizeof(Py_ssize_t) > 4 * PyLong_SHIFT) {
26442  return -(Py_ssize_t) (((((((((size_t)digits[3]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (size_t)digits[2]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (size_t)digits[1]) << PyLong_SHIFT) | (size_t)digits[0]));
26443  }
26444  break;
26445  }
26446  }
26447  #endif
26448  return PyLong_AsSsize_t(b);
26449  }
26450  x = PyNumber_Index(b);
26451  if (!x) return -1;
26452  ival = PyInt_AsSsize_t(x);
26453  Py_DECREF(x);
26454  return ival;
26455 }
